nyone under 18. It is legal to serve an underage person alcohol in a private place, provided it's a limited amount and done in moderation.<ref name=\"swe2010\">{{cite web|url=https://www.riksdagen.se/sv/dokument-lagar/dokument/svensk-forfattningssamling/alkohollag-20101622_sfs-2010-1622|title=3 Kap. 7\u00a7 Alkohollag (2010:1622)|publisher=|accessdate=27 June 2018}}</ref> The reason for the lower limit in bars than in Systembolaget shops is that bartenders have a legal responsibility for how drunk a guest gets.<ref name=\"sweden\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Switzerland}}\n|{{flag|Switzerland}} (federal law)\n| colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |16 <sup>(fermented beverages with up to 15% ABV and natural wines with up to 18% ABV)</sup><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/20050153/index.html#a11 |title=817.02 Lebensmittel- und Gebrauchsgegenst\u00e4ndeverordnung Art. 11 |publisher=admin.ch |date= |accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref><br /> 18 <sup>(spirits)</sup><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/19320035/index.html#a41 |title=680 Bundesgesetz \u00fcber die gebrannten Wasser Art. 41 IV. 1. i. |publisher=admin.ch |date= |accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n| Whoever offers or supplies alcohol beverages to a child under the age of 16 years in an amount which is harmful to one's health is punished with imprisonment up to 3 years or a fine.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/19370083/201501010000/311.0.pdf |title=311.0 Schweizerisches Strafgesetzbuch vom 21. Dezember 1937 (Stand am 1. Januar 2015) - Art. 411 |author= |date= |language=de |website=admin.ch |page= |publisher=Swiss Federal Council |access-date=2015-08-09}}</ref> Whoever sells or supplies spirits to a person under the age of 18 years is punished with a fine up to 10.000 CHF.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/19320035/index.html#a57 |title=680 Bundesgesetz vom 21. Juni 1932 \u00fcber die gebrannten Wasser (Alkoholgesetz) - Art. 57 |author= |date= |language=de |website=admin.ch |page= |publisher=Swiss Federal Council |access-date=2015-08-09}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flag|Ticino}}\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18\n| Canton [[Ticino]] prohibits the selling of any type of alcohol beverage to minors under the age of 18.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www3.ti.ch/CAN/RLeggi/public/index.php/raccolta-leggi/pdfatto/atto/628 |title=RL 942.100 Legge sugli esercizi alberghieri e sulla ristorazione del 1\u00b0 giugno 2010 (stato 15 giugno 2017) - art. 23 cpv. 1 lit. a |language=it |website=ti.ch |accessdate=2019-03-02}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Turkey}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mevzuat.gov.tr/MevzuatMetin/1.3.4250.pdf|title=\u0130SP\u0130RTO VE \u0130SP\u0130RTOLU \u0130\u00c7K\u0130LER \u0130NH\u0130SARI KANUNU|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n|{{See also|Alcohol laws of Turkey}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Ukraine}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|Law No. 1824-VI on state regulation of production and turnover of ethyl, cognac and fruit, alcoholic beverages and tobacco products Article 15-3\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |{{flag|United Kingdom}}\n|{{flag|England}} <br /> {{flag|Wales}}\n| align=\"center\" | None / 5<ref name=\"uk\" />\n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"uk\" /> 16 <sup>(beer, wine or cider with meal and if accompanied by adult)</sup><ref name=\"scotland\" />\n| align=\"center\" | 18 <ref name=\"uk\" /> \n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"uk\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2003/17/contents|title=Licensing Act 2003|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n|\n* It is prohibited to sell, serve, or offer alcohol beverages in licensed premises under the age of 18,<ref name=\"uk\" /> but minors aged 16\u201317 may consume wine, beer or cider on licensed premises when ordered with a meal and they are accompanied by an adult. Minors are prohibited to consume alcohol beverages in public.\n* Import: People over 17 are entitled to a duty-free allowance for alcohol beverages.\n|-\n|{{flag|Scotland}}\n| style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"scotland\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/alcohol-young-people-law|title=Alcohol and young people - GOV.UK|last=|first=|date=|website=www.gov.uk|accessdate=2019-10-22}}</ref> 16 <sup>(beer, wine or cider with meal if accompanied by adult))</sup><ref name=\"scotland\" />\n| align=\"center\" | 18\n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"scotland\" />\n|\n* It is prohibited to sell, serve, or offer alcohol beverages to anyone under the age of 18, but minors aged 16\u201317 may consume wine, beer or cider on licensed premises when ordered with a meal and they are accompanied by an adult. Minors are prohibited to consume alcohol beverages in public.<ref name=\"Licensing Act 2005\">{{cite web|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/asp/2005/16/part/8/crossheading/offences-relating-to-children-and-young-people|title=Licensing (Scotland) Act 2005|publisher=|accessdate=28 July 2015}}</ref>\n*Import: People over 17 are entitled to a duty-free allowance for alcohol beverages.<ref name=\"UK Duty Free\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/duty-free-goods/arrivals-from-outside-the-eu|title=Bringing goods into the UK - 3. Arrivals from outside the EU|website=gov.uk|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flag|Northern Ireland|union}}\n| style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" | 18\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | 18\n|It is prohibited to sell, serve, or offer alcohol beverages to anyone under the age of 18. Minors are prohibited to consume alcohol beverages in public.\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" |{{flag|United Kingdom}}\n|Under the [[British Beer and Pub Association|BBPA]]'s [[Challenge 21|Challenge 21 and Challenge 25]] schemes, customers attempting to buy alcohol beverages are asked to prove their age if in the retailer's opinion they look under 21<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beerandpub.com/industry-briefings/challenge-21|title=BBPA Home - Industry Briefings - Challenge 21|publisher=}}</ref> (or optionally 25) even though the law states they must be a minimum of 18. Many supermarket and off-licence chains display Challenge 21 (or Challenge 25) notices stating that they will not serve people who look under 21 (or 25) without ID.\n|}\n\n==Oceania==\n[[File:Alkoholersterwerbsalter in Ozeanien.png|thumb|230px|'''Minimum legal age to purchase alcohol by country (2015):'''<br />{{legend|#7F0000|Minimum purchase age of 21 years}}{{legend|#0026FF|Minimum purchase age of 18 years}}{{legend|#808080|No minimum purchase age}}|alt=]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:75%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:15%;\"| Country\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:15%;\"| State/region/province\n! colspan=2 style=\"width:30%;\"| [[De jure]]\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:40%;\"| Notes\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Drinking age\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Purchase age\n|-\n| United States\n|''{{flag|American Samoa}}''\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 21<ref>{{cite web|title=ALCOHOL REFORM ISSUES PAPER|url=http://www.samoalawreform.gov.ws/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Alcohol-Reform-Issues-Paper-Final.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140917184910/http://www.samoalawreform.gov.ws/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Alcohol-Reform-Issues-Paper-Final.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-date=17 September 2014|website=samoalawreform.gov.ws|publisher=Samoa Law Reform Commission|accessdate=25 March 2015}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Australia}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Varies by state.\n|18<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|{{main|Alcohol laws of Australia}}All states restrict purchasing to over 18, but exceptions may apply if accompanied by a parent or guardian. The government-supported Youth Law Australia portal offers details on consumption and supply age limits by state.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://yla.org.au/nsw/topics/teen-issues/alcohol/|title=Teen issues: Alcohol|last=|first=|date=|website=Youth Law Australia|publisher=Department of Health Victoria|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Fiji}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 18<ref name=\"Fiji\">{{cite web|url=https://www.laws.gov.fj/Acts/DisplayAct/273|title=Liquor Act 2006|last=|first=|date=2018-08-01|website=|publisher=Fijitimes.com|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref>\n| The drinking age was previously 21 but was lowered to 18 in 2009.<ref name=\"Fiji\"/>\n|-\n| United States\n|''{{flag|Guam}}''\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | 18\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{flag|Micronesia, Federated States of}}\n| {{flag|Chuuk}} <br /> {{flag|Kosrae}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 18<ref>Draft Chuuk State Code (2012) Section 1307(1) - unenacted draft code citing source laws</ref><ref>Kosrae State Code (1997), Sections S.1.201(44) and 13.517(3)</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Pohnpei}} <br /> {{flag|Yap}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 21<ref>Code of the State of Pohnpei (2012), Section 2-109</ref><ref>Yap State Code (1987), Section 405</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|New Zealand}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| None || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 18<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alcohol.org.nz/management-laws/nz-alcohol-laws/sale-and-supply-of-alcohol-act-2012|title=Sale and Supply of Alcohol Act 2012|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=alcohol.org.nz|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref>\n| Minimum age applies for beverages with 1.15% ABV or over; no restrictions on beverages less than 1.15% ABV.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.legislation.govt.nz/act/public/1989/0063/latest/DLM165121.html#DLM165121 |title= 2 Interpretation -- Sale of Liquor Act 1989 No 63 (as at 01 July 2011), Public Act -- New Zealand Legislation Online |publisher=Parliamentary Counsel Office |date=1 July 2011 |accessdate=2013-01-08}}</ref><br>Persons under 18 may drink outside private residences or private functions if accompanied by their parent or legal guardian. Alcohol may be supplied to minors only by, or with express consent from, their parent or legal guardian.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://alcohol.org.nz/help-advice/advice-on-alcohol/for-parents/the-law-about-supply-to-young-people |title=The law about supply to young people |publisher=Alcohol.org.nz |accessdate=30 April 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| United States\n|''{{flag|Northern Mariana Islands}}''\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|21<ref name=\"Northern Mariana Islands Public Law 19-84\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cnmilaw.org/pdf/public_laws/19/pl19-84.pdf|title=H. B. No. 19-141 HDI SSI|publisher=cnmilaw.org|accessdate=22 March 2018}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Palau}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 21<ref name=\"Palau Alcoholic Beverage Control Act\">{{cite web|url=http://www.paclii.org/pw/legis/consol_act/babrt11389/|title=Alcoholic Beverage Control Act - \u00a7 1068. Sale or distribution to minors; purchase, possession, or consumption by minors.|publisher=Pacific Islands Legal Information Institute|accessdate=22 March 2018}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell or serve any alcohol beverage to a person under 21 years of age. Minors may access a bar or licensed premises only if accompanied by a parent or legal guardian. Minors buying, consuming or attempting to buy alcohol are committing an offence. The law provides an exception for the consumption of alcohol by minors as part of a religiously recognized ceremony.<ref name=\"Palau Alcoholic Beverage Control Act\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Papua New Guinea}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 18{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n| It is prohibited for a minor to purchase, consume or attempt to purchase alcohol beverages. Any licence holder has to ensure that the customer who he sells or serves alcohol to, is at least 18 years of age. Violation of this law is punishable by a fine.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}  ''Liquor Licensing Act (1963) Art 102-103''\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Samoa}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 21<ref name=\"Samoa Liquor Licensing Act\">{{cite web|url=http://www.palemene.ws/new/wp-content/uploads/01.Acts/Acts%202011/Liquor_Act_2011_-_Eng.pdf|title=Liquor Act 2011 - Section 14|publisher=Parliament of Samoa|accessdate=22 March 2018}}</ref>\n| Selling or serving alcohol to a person under the age of 21 years is punishable with a three hundred dollar fine, imprisonment for nine months, or both.<ref name=\"Solomon Islands Liquor Licensing Act\"/> \"does not apply to a licensee of a food and beverage license provided that the person under the age of 21 years is under the supervision of an attending parent.\"\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Solomon Islands}}\n| align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Solomon Islands Liquor Licensing Act\"/>\n| align=\"center\" |21<ref name=\"Solomon Islands Liquor Licensing Act\">{{cite web|url=http://www.paclii.org/sb/criminal-law/ch50-liquor-act.htm|title=Section 72 of the Liquor Act (Ch. 144)|publisher=Pacific Islands Legal Information Institute|accessdate=22 March 2018}}</ref>\n| Selling or serving alcohol to a person under the age of 21 years is punishable with a three hundred dollar fine, imprisonment for nine months, or both.<ref name=\"Solomon Islands Liquor Licensing Act\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''{{flag|Tokelau}}''\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 18<ref>[http://www.paclii.org/cgi-bin/sinodisp/tk/legis/num_act/cpaer2003302/cpaer2003302.html Crimes, Procedure and Evidence Rules 2003], s50(3).</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Tonga}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 18<ref name=\"Tonga Liquor Licensing Act\">{{cite web|url=https://ago.gov.to/cms/images/LEGISLATION/PRINCIPAL/1950/1950-0025/IntoxicatingLiquorAct_2.pdf?zoom_highlight=Intoxicating+Liquor+Act#search=%22Intoxicating%20Liquor%20Act%22|title=INTOXICATING LIQUOR ACT - Section 65|publisher=The Kingdom of Tonga, Attorney General's Office|accessdate=22 March 2018}}</ref>\n| Selling, serving or supplying alcohol to anyone under 18 years is prohibited. It is also prohibited for minors to buy, attempt to buy or consume alcohol in any public place and any violation of this law is punishable by a $1,000 fine.<ref name=\"Tonga Liquor Licensing Act\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Vanuatu}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 18<ref name=\"Vanuatu Liquor Licensing Act\">{{cite web|url=http://www.paclii.org/vu/legis/consol_act/lla190/|title=Liquor Licensing Act - Section 17|publisher=Pacific Islands Legal Information Institute|accessdate=22 March 2018}}</ref>\n| It is unlawful to sell, serve or supply alcohol to any person under the age of 18 years. Violation of the law is fined up to VT 25,000 or by a term of imprisonment not exceeding 3 months, or by both, fine and imprisonment. Any minor under the age of 18 years, being found in possession or consumption of alcohol is fined up to VT 10,000.<ref name=\"Vanuatu Liquor Licensing Act\"/>\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Youth rights sidebar}}\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Amethyst Initiative]]\n* [[Alcohol consumption by youth in the United States]]\n* [[National Minimum Drinking Age Act]]\n* [[Alcoholism]]\n* [[National Youth Rights Association]]\n* [[Shoulder tap (alcohol)]]\n* [[Foundation for Advancing Alcohol Responsibility]]\n* [[Choose Responsibility]]\n* [[Mature minor doctrine]]\n* [[Youth]]\n* [[Youth suffrage]]\n* [[Youth rights]]\n* [[Age of candidacy]]\n* [[Legal drinking age controversy]]\n* [[Smoking age]]\n{{div col end}}\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160504144607/http://www.iard.org/policy-tables/minimum-legal-age-limits/ Minimum legal age limits] online table updated on a rolling basis, [[International Alliance for Responsible Drinking]]\n\n{{Law country lists}}\n{{Alcohol and health}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Legal Drinking Age}}\n[[Category:Alcohol law]]\n[[Category:Drinking culture]]\n[[Category:Juvenile law]]\n[[Category:Law-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists by country]]\n[[Category:Minimum ages]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Alkoholersterwerbsalter (Weltweit)2.svg|thumb|500px|'''Minimum legal age to purchase alcohol by country (2015):'''<br />{{legend|#000000|Prohibited regardless of age}}{{legend|#441200|Minimum age is 25}}{{legend|#7F0000|Minimum age is 21}}{{legend|#FF0000|Minimum age is 20}}{{legend|#B200FF|Minimum age is 19}}{{legend|#0026FF|Minimum age is 18}}{{legend|#00FFFF|Minimum age is 17}}{{legend|#267F00|Minimum age is 16}}{{legend|#00FF00|Minimum age is 15}}{{legend|#B9B9B9|No regulation/no age set}}|alt=]]\n\nThe '''legal drinking age''' is the minimum age at which a person can [[legally]] consume [[alcoholic beverage|alcohol beverage]]s. The minimum age alcohol can be legally consumed can be different from the age when it can be purchased in some countries. These laws vary between different countries and many laws have exemptions or special circumstances. Most laws apply only to [[Drinking in public|drinking alcohol in public places]] with alcohol consumption in the home being mostly unregulated (an exception being the UK, which has a minimum legal age of five for supervised consumption in private places). Some countries also have different age limits for different [[List of alcoholic drinks|types of alcohol drinks]].<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n\nThe most commonly known reason for the law behind the legal drinking age is the [[Long-term impact of alcohol on the brain|effect on the brain]] in adolescents. Since the brain is still maturing, alcohol can have a [[Effects of alcohol on memory|negative effect on the memory]] and long-term thinking. Alongside that, it can cause [[Alcoholic liver disease|liver failure]], and create a [[Long-term effects of alcohol consumption#Hormonal imbalance|hormone imbalance]] in teens due to the constant changes and maturing of hormones during [[puberty]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://pubs.niaaa.nih.gov/publications/AA67/AA67.htm |title=Underage Drinking |publisher=National Institute on Alcohol Abuse and Alcoholism |date=January 2006 |access-date=13 May 2018}}</ref> Young people are also especially at increased risk of injury when drinking alcohol.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Peltzer|date=2015|title=Factors associated with unintentional injury among university students in 26 countries|url=|journal=Public Health Nurs|volume=32|issue=5|pages=440\u2013452|doi=10.1111/phn.12179|pmid=25644243}}</ref>\n\n==Africa==\n[[File:Drinking age Africa.svg|thumb|230px|'''Minimum legal age to purchase alcohol by country (2015):'''<br />{{legend|#000000|Prohibited}}{{legend|#7F0000|Minimum purchase age of 21 years}}{{legend|#0026FF|Minimum purchase age of 18 years}}{{legend|#00FFDD|Minimum purchase age of 17 years}}{{legend|#267F00|Minimum purchase age of 16 years}}{{legend|#00FF00|Minimum purchase age of 15 years}}{{legend|#808080|No minimum purchase age}}|alt=]]\nThe most common minimum age to purchase alcohol in Africa is 18. However, Angola (except Luanda Province), Central African Republic, Comoros, Equatorial Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Mali, and Togo have no laws on the book restricting the sale of alcohol to minors. In Libya, Somalia and Sudan the sale, production and consumption of alcohol is completely prohibited.{{synthesis inline|date=October 2018}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:75%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:15%;\"| Country\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:15%;\"| State/region/province\n! colspan=2 style=\"width:30%;\"| ''[[De jure]]''\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:40%;\"| Notes\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Drinking age\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Purchase age\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Algeria}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | None{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n|18<ref name=\"Icap Reports 4\">[https://www.iard.org/science-resources/detail/Minimum-Legal-Age-Limits Minimum legal age limits] - International Alliance for Responsible Drinking</ref>\n|Order No. 26-75 (1975), Article 14\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| {{flag|Angola}}\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  colspan=\"2\" | None <ref name=\"ACPF: MINIMUM AGE FOR SALE OF ALCOHOL\">{{cite web|url=http://www.africanchildforum.org/clr/Harmonisation%20of%20Laws%20in%20Africa/other-documents-harmonisation_8_en.pdf|title=PROTECTION FROM DRUG ABUSE/ MINIMUM AGE FOR SALE OF ALCOHOL AND DRUGS: INTERNATIONAL AND REGIONAL LAWS|publisher=The African Child Policy Forum|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n| There is no national legislation prohibiting the sale of alcohol to minors.\n|-\n|[[Luanda Province]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=\"2\" | 18<ref name=\"Decreto Executivo n\u00ba 87/08 de 10 julho\">{{cite web|url=http://www.luanda.gov.ao/verlegislacao.aspx?id=434|title=Sobre o acesso de menores a espect\u00e1culos nocturnos, e o consumo e a comercializa\u00e7\u00e3o de bebidas alco\u00f3licas por menores|publisher=Governo Provincial de Luanda|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n| Legislation in [[Luanda Province]]:\nIt is prohibited to sell alcohol beverages to anyone under the age of 18. It is also prohibited for minors to buy and consume alcohol.<ref name=\"Decreto Executivo n\u00ba 87/08 de 10 julho\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | {{flag|Benin}}\n|None\n|20\n|Republic of Benin Report to UN Committee on the Rights of the Child CRC/C/BEN/2 (2005):\n\n* Article 8 of the decree of 10 June 1942 regulating the production, import, advertisement, sale, and consumption of alcohol beverages in French West Africa, prohibits the sale or free supply of alcohol beverages to minors under 20.\n* Article 13 stipulates fines ranging from CFAF 200,000 to CFAF 1 million for such offences, doubled in the case of repeat offences.\n* There are no official measures prohibiting children from consuming alcohol, tobacco or other substances harmful to their health.\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | {{flag|Botswana}}\n| align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Botswana Liquor Act 2008\">{{cite web|url=https://www.a-mla.org/images/acts/LIQOUR%20ACT,%202004.pdf.pdf|title=Liquor Act 2008 - Section 32|publisher=Government of Botswana|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref> <small>(prohibited for any person to supply)</small><ref name=\"ACPF: MINIMUM AGE FOR SALE OF ALCOHOL\" />\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Botswana Liquor Act 2008\" />\n| It is prohibited for any person with a liquor license to sell or supply alcohol beverages to minors under the age of 18 years. Because the law only applies to licensees, it is not prohibited for minors to buy, consume, or possess alcohol beverages.<ref name=\"Botswana Liquor Act 2008\" /> It is also prohibited for any person to expose or supply alcohol to a minor under the age of 18 years.<ref name=\"ACPF: MINIMUM AGE FOR SALE OF ALCOHOL\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | {{flag|Burundi}}\n| align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Code Penal Burundi\">{{cite web|url=https://ihl-databases.icrc.org/applic/ihl/ihl-nat.nsf/0/cb9d300d8db9fc37c125707300338af2/$FILE/Code%20P%C3%A9nal%20du%20Burundi%20.pdf|title=Code P\u00e9nal du Burundi - Article 501 et 502|publisher=MINISTRE DE LA JUSTICE ET GARDE|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" |18 <small>(unless accompanied by parent or legal guardian)</small><ref name=\"Code Penal Burundi\" />\n| It is prohibited for any person with a liquor license to sell or supply alcohol beverages to unaccompanied minors under the age of 18 years.\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Cameroon}}\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" | 21 <small>(18 if accompanied by a person 21 years of age or older)</small><ref name=\"Cameroon Penal Code\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wipo.int/wipolex/fr/text.jsp?file_id=425156|title=Law No. 2016/007 of July 12, 2016, relating to the Penal Code - Section 348|publisher=|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited for any person with a liquor license to sell or supply alcohol beverages to anyone under 18 years of age. The law permits adults from the ages 18 to 21 to consume, purchase and buy alcohol beverages if accompanied by a person 21 years of age or older. Anyone over the age of 21 years may buy or consume alcohol unaccompanied.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Cape Verde}}\n| align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Cap Verde Liquor Law\">{{cite web|url=https://www.minsaude.gov.cv/index.php/documentosite/342-1-plano-alcool-b-o-i-serie-n-29-de-18-de-abril-de-2016/file|title=Lei n.\u00b0 27/V/97|publisher=Imprensa Nacional de Cabo Verde|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Cap Verde Liquor Law\"/>\n| It is prohibited for any person to sell or supply alcohol beverages to minors under the age of 18 years.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Central African Republic}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 15 <small>(off-premises)</small>, or 21 <small>(on-premises)</small><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.who.int/substance_abuse/publications/global_alcohol_report/profiles/caf.pdf|title=WHO Global Alcohol Report Central African Republic|date=2014|website=World Health Organization|access-date=18 October 2018}}</ref>\n|It is prohibited for any person to sell or supply alcohol beverages to minors under the age of 15 years when sold or supplied off-premises (e.g., liquor stores, wine stores, and supermarkets). It is prohibited for any person to sell or supply alcohol beverages to minors under the age of 21 years when sold or supplied on-premises (e.g., restaurants, bars, and cafes).<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | {{flag|Chad}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18\n|Law 2017-01 Penal Code Chapter 6 Articles 376-378 establish penalties for licensees who permit entry to youth below age 16 unaccompanied by a supervising adult, sell or offer alcohol beverages to youth below age