=dead}}</ref>\n|Decree 54/2013 Regulations on the Control of the Production, Sale and Consumption of Alcoholic Beverages (2013), Article 5 (Prohibitions)\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Namibia}}\n| align=\"center\" | None\n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"Namibia Liquor Act 6 of 1998\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lac.org.na/laws/annoREG/Liquor%20Act%206%20of%201998%20-%20Regulations%202001-142%20(annotated).pdf|title=Liquor Act 6 of 1998 |publisher=\tLegal Assistance Centre|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell, serve or supply alcohol beverages to anyone under the age of 18 years.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Niger}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=2| 18\n|Penal Code Article 302\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Nigeria}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=2| None (at national level)<ref name=\"ACPF: MINIMUM AGE FOR SALE OF ALCOHOL\"/>\n|Purchase age of 18 in Abuja (Abuja Municipal Area Council Bye-Law 2001 Sec 15)\n\nProhibited in Borno state\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Republic of the Congo}}\n| align=\"center\" | None\n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"LOI N\u00b0 4-2010 DU 14 JUIN 2010\">{{cite web|url=https://www.unicef.org/wcaro/wcaro_CONG_childprotection_framework_2010.pdf|title=LOI N\u00b0 4-2010 DU 14 JUIN 2010 Article 123|publisher=UNICEF|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Rwanda}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=2|18\n|Organic Law implementing the Penal Code N\u00b001/2012/OL Articles 217 and 219\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Senegal}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|18<ref name=\"N\u00b0 3097/MINT/DAGAT/DEL/DB\">{{cite web|url=http://www.servicepublic.gouv.sn/assets/textes/debits_de_boisson.pdf|title=N\u00b0 3097/MINT/DAGAT/DEL/DB|publisher=REPUBLIQUE DU SENEGAL MINISTRE DE L\u2019INTERIEUR|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Seychelles}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | None\n|18\n|\nChapter 113 Licenses Act (2010)\n\n* Subsidiary Legislation: Licenses (Manufacturing) Regulation (1987), Article 8(5)(page 20):\n** In the case of manufacturing and processing of liquor, tobacco and tobacco products, the license holder shall (i) not deliver or sell liquor to, or allow any consumption of liquor by, any person under the age of 18 years or deliver or sell tobacco or tobacco products or allow it to be used on the premises by such a person;\n* Subsidiary Legislation: Licenses (Liquor and Outdoor Entertainment) Regulations (1998), Article 14 (page 28):\n** (1) The holder of a license, his servant or agent shall not (a) employ or allow a person under the age of 18 years, ... (b) sell or deliver liquor, cigarettes or tobacco products to, or allow liquor to be consumed or cigarettes or any tobacco products to be used by any person under the age of 18 years on the premises; ... (i) admit any person under the age of 18 years to a premises licensed as a public bar, toddy bar or at the premises licensed to manufacture and sell baka or lapire;...\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Somalia}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| Prohibited<ref name=\"Acsom\">{{cite web|title=Alcohol - Somalia|url=http://www.who.int/substance_abuse/publications/global_alcohol_report/profiles/som.pdf|publisher=WHO|accessdate=29 November 2014}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|South Africa}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|18\n| The parent, adult guardian of a minor or a person responsible for administering a religious sacrament, may on occasion supply to that minor a moderate quantity of liquor to be consumed by the minor in the presence and under the supervision of that parent, guardian or other person.<ref>{{cite journal |author=Department of Trade & Industry |journal=Government Gazette |volume=446 |issue=26294 |date=26 April 2004 |url=http://www.thedti.gov.za/business_regulation/docs/nla/act2003.pdf |title=The National Liquor Act, 59 of 2003 |accessdate=2013-01-08}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|South Sudan}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref name=\"ACPF: MINIMUM AGE FOR SALE OF ALCOHOL\"/>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Sudan}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| Prohibited<ref>{{cite web|url=https://travel.state.gov/travel/cis_pa_tw/cis/cis_1029.html|title=Sudan: Country Specific Information|publisher=[[U.S. Department of State]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111012511/http://travel.state.gov/travel/cis_pa_tw/cis/cis_1029.html|archivedate=2014-01-11}}</ref>\n|Penal Code 1991, Art 78-79\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Tanzania}}\n| align=\"center\" | None\n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"Tanzania Law of the Child Act 2009\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mcdgc.go.tz/data/Law_of_the_Child_Act_2009.pdf|title=Law of the Child Act 2009 - Section 17 |publisher=Tanzania Ministry of Health, Community Development, Gender, Elderly and Children|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Togo}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|None<ref name=\"ACPF: MINIMUM AGE FOR SALE OF ALCOHOL\"/>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Tunisia}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|Sale to Muslims is prohibited;\n16/18 for others\n|Law 59-147 Regulation of beverage outlets and similar establishments as modified by Law 74-23 Article 35 prohibits serving alcohol beverages to Muslims and entry to on-premise establishments to persons under 16 years of age unaccompanied by a parent or responsible adult;\n\nLaw 2004-75 Article 4 prohibits entry to night clubs to those under 18 with an exception for accompanied persons between 16 and 18 in certain venues, sale of alcohol beverages to whom is prohibited.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Uganda}}\n| align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Liquor Act 1960, Uganda\">{{cite web|url=https://ulii.org/ug/legislation/consolidated-act/93|title=Liquor Act 1960 - Section 19|publisher=Uganda Legal Information Institute|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" |18<br/>16 <sup>(wine, beer, porter, cider, perry or native liquor with meal)</sup><ref name=\"Liquor Act 1960, Uganda\"/>\n| It is prohibited for any licensee to sell, serve or supply alcohol beverages to anyone under the age of 18 years. The law provides an exception for anyone who is 16 or 17 years of age, and consumes a fermented alcohol drink with a meal, in a part of a licensed premises that serves meals and is not a bar.\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''{{flag|Western Sahara}}''\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| None<ref name=\"ACPF: MINIMUM AGE FOR SALE OF ALCOHOL\"/>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Zambia}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=2| 18<ref name=\"Liquor Licensing Act 2011, Zambia\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.gov.zm/sites/default/files/documents/acts/Liqour%20Licensing%20Act%2C%202011.pdf|title=THE LIQUOR LICENSING ACT, 2011 - Section 36|publisher=Government of Zambia|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited for any person with a liquor license, to sell, serve or supply alcohol beverages to anyone under 18 years of age. Before the Liquor Licensing Act was enacted in 2011, the minimum age to sell, serve and supply alcohol beverages was 14 years.<ref>The Liquor Act, 1959 - Section 46</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Zimbabwe}}\n| align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"CHILDREN\u2019S ACT ZIMBABWE\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ilo.org/dyn/natlex/docs/ELECTRONIC/76958/88827/F-860336063/ZWE76958.pdf|title=CHILDREN'S ACT - Section 78|publisher=International Labour Organisation|accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" |18 (except with parent/guardian consent)<br />\n| Liquor Act Article 116 Prohibited conduct by persons in general (1) No person shall\u2014 ... (l) being a person to whom in terms of this Act the sale of liquor is prohibited, purchase or attempt to purchase liquor in contravention of such provision; .... (o) sell, lend, give, supply or deliver, or offer so to do, any liquor to any person under the age of eighteen years except with the consent of the parent or guardian of that person.\n\nChildren's Act Section 78 - It is prohibited for any person to sell, lend, give, supply, deliver or offer alcohol beverages to any child under the age of 16 years, except upon production of a written order signed by the parent or guardian of the child known to such person. The police has the duty to seize any alcohol beverage in the possession of a child under the age of 16 years without a written consent of the parents or legal guardian.<ref name=\"CHILDREN\u2019S ACT ZIMBABWE\" />\n|}\n\n==Americas==\n[[File:Drinking age North America.svg|thumb|230px|'''Minimum legal age to purchase alcohol by country:'''<br />{{legend|#7F0000|Minimum purchase age of 21 years}}{{legend|#B200FF|Minimum purchase age of 19 years}}{{legend|#0026FF|Minimum purchase age of 18 years}}]]\n[[File:Alkoholersterwerbsalter in Zentralamerika und der Karibik.png|thumb|230px|'''Minimum legal age to purchase alcohol by country:'''<br />{{legend|#0026FF|Minimum purchase age of 18 years}}{{legend|#267F00|Minimum purchase age of 16 years}}]]\n[[File:Drinking age South America.svg|thumb|230px|'''Minimum legal age to purchase alcohol by country (2015):'''<br />{{legend|#FF0000|Minimum purchase age of 20 years}}{{legend|#0026FF|Minimum purchase age of 18 years}}|alt=]]\n\nIn [[Central America]], the [[Caribbean]], and [[South America]] the legal drinking age and legal purchase age varies from 0 to 20 years (see table below). In [[South America]] in particular, the legal purchase age is 18 years, with two exceptions:\n* In [[Paraguay]], the legal drinking age and purchase age is 20 years.\n* In [[Guyana]], minors aged 16 or 17 may consume a glass of beer, wine or cider in a restaurant provided they buy a meal.\n\nIn [[North America]] the legal drinking age and legal purchase age varies from 18 to 21 years:\n* In [[Mexico]], it is 18 for each.\n* In the [[United States]], the minimum legal age to purchase any alcohol beverage from a shop, supermarket, liquor store, bar, club or any other licensed premises is 21 years of age; the two exceptions are [[Puerto Rico]] and the [[United States Virgin Islands|Virgin Islands]] where the age is 18. The legal drinking age varies by state.\n* In [[Canada]], most provinces have a minimum age of 19 years to buy or consume alcohol, while [[Alberta]], [[Manitoba]] and [[Quebec]] set it at 18 years.\n\nIn the late twentieth century, much of North America changed its minimum legal drinking ages (MLDAs) as follows: {{Quote|text=In the 1970s, provincial and state policy makers in Canada and the United States moved to lower MLDAs (which were set at 21 years in most provinces/territories and states) to coincide with the jurisdictional [[age of majority]] \u2014 typically 18 years of age.... As a result, MLDAs were reduced in all Canadian provinces [and] in [[U.S. history of alcohol minimum purchase age by state|more than half of US states]]. In Canada, however, two provinces, Ontario [in 1979] and Saskatchewan [in 1976], quickly raised their subsequent MLDAs from 18 to 19 years in response to a few studies demonstrating an association between the lowered drinking age and increases in alcohol-related harms to youth and young adults, including increases in [[motor vehicle accidents]] (MVAs) and [[alcohol intoxication]] among high school students. Following MLDA reductions in the US, research in several states provided persuasive evidence of sharp increases in rates of fatal and nonfatal MVAs appearing immediately after the implementation of lower drinking ages. These scientific findings galvanized public pressure on lawmakers to raise MLDAs and, in response, the federal government introduced the [[National Minimum Drinking Age Act]] of 1984, which imposed a reduction of highway funds for states if they did not increase their MLDA to 21 years. All states complied and implemented an MLDA of 21 years by 1988.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Impacts of drinking-age laws on mortality in Canada, 1980\u20132009|last1=Callaghan|first1=Russell |last2=Sanches|last3=Gatley|last4=Stockwell|journal=Drug and Alcohol Dependence|year=2014|volume=138|pages=137\u201345|doi=10.1016/j.drugalcdep.2014.02.019|pmid=24631002|display-authors=1}}</ref>}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible\" style=\"width:75%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:15%;\"| Country\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:15%;\"| State/region/province\n! colspan=2 style=\"width:30%;\"| [[De jure]]\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:40%;\"| Notes\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Drinking age\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Purchase age\n|-\n| colspan=2|''{{flag|Anguilla}}''\n| align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"L075-00-Liquor Licences Act\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gov.ai/laws/L075-00-Liquor%20Licences%20Act/|title=L075-00-Liquor Licences Act - 27. |publisher=Government of Anguilla|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"L075-00-Liquor Licences Act\"/>\n| It is prohibited to sell or serve alcohol drinks to anyone under the age of 18 years. Violating the regulation is punished with a $9.600 fine.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Antigua and Barbuda}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |16<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.laws.gov.ag/acts/chapters/cap-249.pdf |publisher=laws.gov.ag |title=THE LICENSING (INTOXICATING LIQUOR) ACT - CHAPTER 249 - PART V - 24. |accessdate=2015-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103005432/http://www.laws.gov.ag/acts/chapters/cap-249.pdf |archive-date=2015-01-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| The sale and distribution of alcohol to a person under 16 years of age, and purchase by persons under 16 years of age, for consumption in licensed premises are prohibited.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Argentina}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|18<ref>{{cite web|url=http://servicios.infoleg.gob.ar/infolegInternet/anexos/40000-44999/42480/norma.htm|title=Ley Nacional De Lucha Contra El Alcoholismo|last=|first=|date=31 March 1997|website=|language=Spanish|accessdate=7 October 2019}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Bahamas}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref>{{cite web |url=http://laws.bahamas.gov.bs/cms/images/LEGISLATION/PRINCIPAL/2007/2007-0001/ChildProtectionAct_1.pdf |publisher=Government of the Bahamas |title=CHILD PROTECTION ACT - PART VI - CARE AND PROTECTION OF CHILDREN SUPERVISION ORDERS - 62. (4) |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited for any adult to sell, serve or supply any alcohol beverage to a child (defined as anyone under the age of 18 years). The law provides an exception to treat an illness in urgent cases or upon order by a medical doctor.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Barbados}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |16<ref name=\"Barbados Advocate - Drinking Age\">{{cite news |url=https://www.barbadosadvocate.com/news/raise-drinking-age |publisher=BARBADOS ADVOCATE |title=RAISE DRINKING AGE |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell or serve any alcohol beverage to anyone under the age of 16 years. The President of the Barbados Road Safety Association is trying to raise the drinking age to 18 years because the law is often violated.<ref name=\"Barbados Advocate - Drinking Age\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Belize}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref name=\"Liquor Licences Act BVI\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ird.gov.vg/Portals/0/Liquor%20Licences%20Act%20%28Cap.%20106%29.pdf |publisher=ird.gov.vg |title=Liquor Licences Act (Cap. 106) - PART IV - 34: Sale of intoxicating liquor to children. |accessdate=2015-01-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103005633/http://www.ird.gov.vg/Portals/0/Liquor%20Licences%20Act%20%28Cap.%20106%29.pdf |archivedate=2015-01-03 }}</ref>\n|Drinking age is rarely enforced. IDs are almost never requested.\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''{{flag|Bermuda}}''\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref name=\"Liquor Licences Act Bermuda\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cada.bm/images/articles/Bermuda_Liquor_Licence_Act_1974_-_with_2010_amendments_incorporated.pdf |publisher=cada.bm |title=LIQUOR LICENCE ACT 1974 - Procuring drink for drunken person or minor 42. |accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell or serve any alcohol beverage to a child under the age of 18 years.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Bolivia}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18\n| It is prohibited to sell or serve alcohol beverages to minors under the age of 18 years.\nLaw 259 Against the Sale and Consumption of Alcoholic Beverages (2012) Article 20\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Brazil}}\n| align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Brazil Lei 13.106/2015\">{{cite web|url=http://www.planalto.gov.br/ccivil_03/_ato2015-2018/2015/lei/l13106.htm |title=LEI N\u00ba 13.106, DE 17 DE MAR\u00c7O DE 2015. Art. 1o, Art. 2o |publisher=Presid\u00eancia da Rep\u00fablica Casa Civil|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Brazil Lei 13.106/2015\"/>\n| It is prohibited to sell, serve or supply any alcohol beverage to a person under 18 years of age. The presidential law enacted on March 17, 2015 made any violation of the law a criminal offence. Any adult person selling, serving, giving or supplying alcohol beverages to a minor is punished with imprisonment of 2 to 4 years, a fine of R$3.000 to R$10.000 and a ban to operate any business selling or serving alcohol.\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''{{flag|British Virgin Islands}}''\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|16<ref name=\"Liquor Licences Act BVI\"/>\n| It is prohibited to sell or to supply alcohol to anyone under the age of 16.\n|-\n| rowspan=2| {{flag|Canada}}\n| {{flag|Alberta}}<br/>{{flag|Manitoba}}<br/>{{flag|Quebec}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref name=\"Alberta GAMING AND LIQUOR ACT\"/><ref name=\"Manitoba The Liquor and Gaming Control Act\"/><ref name=\"Quebec ACT RESPECTING LIQUOR PERMITS\"/>\n| In Alberta no person may give or sell or permit any person to give or sell liquor to a minor in licensed premises.<ref name=\"Alberta GAMING AND LIQUOR ACT\">{{cite web|url=http://www.qp.alberta.ca/documents/Acts/g01.pdf |title=GAMING AND LIQUOR ACT - Supplying liquor to minor - 75 |publisher=Alberta Queen\u2019s Printer|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref> In Manitoba a person must not give, sell or otherwise supply liquor to a minor. The law provides exceptions for a doctor, dentist, pharmacist or other health care professional for medical purposes; for sacramental purposes and by the parent, guardian, spouse or common-law partner, if it is given or supplied in a residence.<ref name=\"Manitoba The Liquor and Gaming Control Act\">{{cite web|url=http://web2.gov.mb.ca/laws/statutes/ccsm/l153e.php |title=The Liquor and Gaming Control Act - No providing liquor to minors - 62 (1) and (2)|publisher=Manitoba Queen\u2019s Printer|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref> In Quebec the law prohibits the sale of alcohol beverages to a minor under the age of 18 years.<ref name=\"Quebec ACT RESPECTING LIQUOR PERMITS\">{{cite web|url=http://legisquebec.gouv.qc.ca/en/ShowDoc/cs/P-9.1 |title=ACT RESPECTING LIQUOR PERMITS|publisher=Gouvernement du Qu\u00e9bec|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Ontario}}<br/>{{flag|Saskatchewan}}<br/>{{flag|British Columbia}}<br/>{{flag|Newfoundland and Labrador}}<br/>{{flag|Nova Scotia}}<br/>{{flag|New Brunswick}}<br/>{{flag|Prince Edward Island}}<br/>{{flag|Northwest Territories}}<br/>{{flag|Yukon}}<br/>{{flag|Nunavut}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|19\n| Ontario's [[Liquor Licence Act (Ontario)|Liquor Licence Act]] permits the supply and consumption of liquor to those under the age of 19. However, supplying a person under the age of 19 is restricted to the person's parent or legal guardian, and may only occur in a residence or in a private place of the parent or legal guardian. A person under the age of 19 who was supplied liquor in this manner is permitted to consume the liquor only in the place it was supplied.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ontario.ca/laws/statute/90l19#BK34|title=Liquor Licence Act, R.S.O. 1990, c. L.19 s.30 Rules, persons under 19|publisher=Queen's Printer for Ontario|accessdate=16 October 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''{{flag|Cayman Islands}}''\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref name=\"LIQUOR LICENSING LAW\">{{cite web |url=http://www.gov.ky/pls/portal/docs/PAGE/CIGHOME/FIND/ORGANISATIONS/AZAGENCIES/POL/INFORMATIONGUIDES/FREQUENTLYCONSULTEDLAWS/LIQUOR2000.PDF |publisher=gov.ky |title=LIQUOR LICENSING LAW - 21., 22. |accessdate=2015-01-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150912014454/http://www.gov.ky/pls/portal/docs/PAGE/CIGHOME/FIND/ORGANISATIONS/AZAGENCIES/POL/INFORMATIONGUIDES/FREQUENTLYCONSULTEDLAWS/LIQUOR2000.PDF |archivedate=2015-09-12 }}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell, serve or supply alcohol beverages to anyone under the age of 18 years. It is also prohibited for any minor to buy, attempt to buy or consume alcohol beverages. Violation of the law is punished with a fine of five thousand dollars, and the court may, if the offence was committed by the licensee, order that the licensee shall forfeit his licence and that no licence may be issued to that person for a period not exceeding ten years from the date of his conviction.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Chile}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref name=\"IARD\">{{cite web|url=https://www.iard.org/science-resources/detail/Minimum-Legal-Age-Limits|title=Minimum Legal Age Limits|last=|first=|date=January 2019|website=IARD|accessdate=2019-10-18}}</ref>\n| The minimum age is 18 to enter an enclosure that sells alcohol beverages. Selling alcohol to a minor may incur a fine. One must provide identification upon request. Residents of Chile over the age of 18 must carry their [[identity card#Chile|Chilean identification card]] issued by the Civil Registry and Identification Service at all times.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.leychile.cl/Navegar?idNorma=220208 |title=LAW ON EXPENDITURE AND CONSUMPTION OF ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES |language=Spanish |accessdate=7 September 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Colombia}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Colombia LEY 124 DE 1994\">{{cite web |url=http://www.alcaldiabogota.gov.co/sisjur/normas/Norma1.jsp?i=291 |publisher=Secretar\u00eda Jur\u00eddica Distrital de la Alcald\u00eda Mayor de Bogot\u00e1 D.C |title=LEY 124 DE 1994 - Art\u00edculo 1\u00ba. |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n| The law prohibits the sale of alcohol to a minor (anyone under the age of 18 years). It is not prohibited for minors to buy, attempt to buy or consume alcohol.<ref name=\"Colombia LEY 124 DE 1994\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Costa Rica}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Costa Rica Ley n.\u00ba 7633\">{{cite web |url=http://www.tse.go.cr/pdf/normativa/leyderegulaciondehorarios.pdf |publisher=Secretar\u00eda Jur\u00eddica Distrital de la Alcald\u00eda Mayor de Bogot\u00e1 D.C |title=Ley n.\u00ba 7633 - REGULACI\u00d3N DE HORARIOS DE FUNCIONAMIENTO EN EXPENDIOS DE BEBIDAS ALCOH\u00d3LICAS - ART\u00cdCULO 5.-|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n| The law prohibits the sale of alcohol to a minor (anyone under the age of 18 years). Selling alcohol to a minor will be punished with a fine equivalent to ten basic salaries. Whoever permits minors to maintain in any establishment which main purpose is to sell alcohol beverages, will be sanctioned with a fine equivalent to five salaries. It is not prohibited for minors to buy, attempt to buy or consume alcohol.<ref name=\"Costa Rica Ley n.\u00ba 7633\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Cuba}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |16<ref name=\"Cuba CODIGO PENAL\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gacetaoficial.gob.cu/html/ipenal.html |publisher=gacetaoficial.gob.cu |title=CODIGO PENAL - ARTICULO 313.1.- |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n| The penal code prohibits any adult to induce any young person under the age of 16 years, to habitually consume alcohol beverages. However this means that de facto anyone selling, serving or supplying alcohol should check if the buyer has attained the age of 16 years. In most cases this law is not strictly enforced.<ref name=\"Cuba CODIGO PENAL\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cubahora.cu/sociedad/tragos-amargos |publisher=CUBAHORA |title=Tragos amargos |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | {{flag|Dominica}}\n|None\n|16\n|Laws of Dominica Liquor Licences Act Chapter 70:03, Part IV, Sec 15(f)\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Dominican Republic}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Alcohol y menores\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cnd.com.do/index.php/alcohol-y-menores/introduccion |publisher=cnd.com.do |title=Alcohol y menores de edad |accessdate=2015-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103005732/http://www.cnd.com.do/index.php/alcohol-y-menores/introduccion |archive-date=2015-01-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Ecuador}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Ley Ecuador\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dpe.gob.ec/wp-content/dpetransparencia2014/literala/BaseLegalQueRigeLaInstitucion/ReglamentoLeyOrganicaConsumidor.pdf |publisher=Secretario General de la Administraci\u00f3n P\u00fablica |title=REGLAMENTO GENERAL A LA LEY ORGANICA DE DEFENSA DEL CONSUMIDOR PUBLICADA EN EL SUPLEMENTO DEL REGISTRO OFICIAL No. 116 DEL 10 DE JULIO DEL 2000. - Art. 54.- b) |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell alcohol beverages to a minor under the age of 18 years of age. The law obligates establishments to place a visible notice at the point of sale and to check identification to enforce the law. However it is not prohibited for minors to buy, attempt to buy or consume alcohol.<ref name=\"Ley Ecuador\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|El Salvador}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"LEY REGULADORA DE LA PRODUCCION Y COMERCIALIZACION DEL ALCOHOL Y DE LAS BEBIDAS ALCOHOLICAS\">{{cite web|url=https://sansalvador.gob.sv/phocadownload/userupload/Sindicatura/LEY-REGULADORA-DE-LA-PRODUCCION-Y-COMERCIALIZACION-DE-ALCOHOL-Y-BEBIDAS-ALCOHOLICAS.pdf |publisher=Gobierno de San Salvador |title=LEY REGULADORA DE LA PRODUCCION Y COMERCIALIZACION DEL ALCOHOL Y DE LAS BEBIDAS ALCOHOLICAS - Art. 49.-|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n| It is strictly prohibited to sell or serve alcohol beverages to a minor under the age of 18 years. Violation of the law is punished with \u00a2 25,000.00 and if convicted once more the license will be suspended for a period of six months. It is legal for minors to buy, attempt to buy and consume alcohol.<ref name=\"LEY REGULADORA DE LA PRODUCCION Y COMERCIALIZACION DEL ALCOHOL Y DE LAS BEBIDAS ALCOHOLICAS\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2|''{{flag|Falkland Islands}}''\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref name=\"Control of Drinking by Juveniles Ordinance 1993\">{{cite web|url=https://www.legislation.gov.fk/view/whole/inforce/2018-03-18/fiord-1993-3?query=((Repealed%253DN%2520AND%2520DocType%253D%2522fiord%2522%2520AND%2520PitValid%253D%2540pointInTime(20180318174407)%2520AND%2520DocStatus%253D%2522inforce%2522)%2520OR%2520(Repealed%253DN%2520AND%2520DocType%253D%2522fisl%2522%2520AND%2520PitValid%253D%2540pointInTime(20180318174407)%2520AND%2520DocStatus%253D%2522inforce%2522))%2520AND%2520Year%253D1993&displayQuery=[{%22name%22:%22Document%20types%22,%22value%22:%22In%20force%20Ordinances,%20In%20force%20Secondary%20Legislation%22},{%22name%22:%22Query%22},{%22name%22:%22Year%22,%22value%22:%221993%22,%22operator%22:%22AND%22},{%22name%22:%22Number%22,%22operator%22:%22AND%22},{%22name%22:%22Point%20in%20time%22,%22value%22:%2218/03/2018%22,%22operator%22:%22AND%22}]#sec.4|publisher=Government of the Falkland Islands |title=Control of Drinking by Juveniles Ordinance 1993 - Sections 3, 4 and 5|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited for any adult to sell, give or provide alcohol to a minor under the age of 18 years in any public place or licensed premises. Parents may permit their children to consume alcohol on private premises. Minors consuming alcohol in public are committing a criminal offence. The law provides exceptions for the consumption of alcohol by minors for prescription of or at the direction of a government medical officer or in the course of the administration of Holy Communion according to the rites of any Christian denomination.<ref name=\"Control of Drinking by Juveniles Ordinance 1993\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Grenada}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|16 (None off-premise)\n|Chapter 174 Liquor Dealers' Licenses Act (1988), accessible through the Laws of Grenada Portal\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Guatemala}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref name=\"Guatemala DECRETO NUMERO 90-97\">{{cite web |url=http://www.bvsde.paho.org/bvsacd/cd38/Guatemala/D90-97.pdf |publisher=EL CONGRESO DE LA REPUBLICA DE GUATEMALA |title=DECRETO NUMERO 90-97 - ARTICULO 50.  |accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell, serve or supply any alcohol drink to a minor under 18 years of age. Minors under 18 years are prohibited by law, to consume alcohol beverages in public.<ref name=\"Guatemala DECRETO NUMERO 90-97\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Guyana}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|18\n\n(16 on-premise for wine or malt liquor with a meal)<ref name=\"Guyana Intoxicating Liquor Licensing Act\">{{cite web|url=http://www.guyaneselawyer.com/lawsofguyana/Laws/cap8221.pdf|title=Intoxicating Liquor Licensing Act - Section 55|publisher=EL CONGRESO DE LA REPUBLICA DE GUATEMALA|accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n|It is prohibited to sell or serve alcohol to a person under 18 years of age. The law provides an exception for minors aged 16 and 17, if they consume a glass of beer, wine or cider with a meal in a restaurant. Otherwise attempting to buy alcohol or buying alcohol as a minor is an offence.<ref name=\"Guyana Intoxicating Liquor Licensing Act\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Haiti}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |None (at national level)\n| In the capital Port-au-Prince, it is prohibited to sell or serve alcohol to minors under 18 years old from May 17, 2017. Vendors are required to check identification.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.anmwe.com/haiti-interdiction-de-vendre-de-lalcool-aux-mineurs-informe-le-chef-du-parquet/|title=HAITI: Interdiction de vendre de l'alcool aux mineurs informe le chef du parquet|last=|first=|date=2015-05-22|website=|publisher=Anmwe News|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref> The Senate voted on a proposed Law on the protection of minors from alcohol beverages, to establish a legal purchase age of 18 and related implementation measures, in December 2012. The law has not yet been approved and enacted.\n\n''Law prohibiting minors entry to entertainment venues'' Article 1 prohibits those under the age of 16 from entering cinemas and theaters (except during children's programming), clubs, cafes, or venues licensed to sell alcohol beverages.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Honduras}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|18\n|Law for Police Enforcement and Social Coexistence Decree 226 (2001) Article 68 bans the sale of alcohol to minors; The definition of punishable gang activity for minors aged 12\u201318 includes drinking alcohol beverages in public places (Art 90-91).\n\nCode of Children and Adolescents Decree 73 (1996)\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Jamaica}}\n| align=center|None\n| align=center|18<ref name=\"Child Care and Protection Act Jamaica\">{{cite web|url=http://moj.gov.jm/sites/default/files/laws/Child%20Care%20and%20Protection%20Act_0.pdf |publisher=Government of Jamaica |title=Child Care and Protection Act - Section 40 |accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell or serve any alcohol beverage to a child (which is defined as anyone under the age of 18 years).<ref name=\"Child Care and Protection Act Jamaica\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Mexico}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref name=\"IARD\"/>\n| The minimum age to buy and consume alcohol beverages is regulated by each state of Mexico. But all states have set a minimum age of 18 years, and in no state is it legal for minors to buy and consume alcohol.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Nicaragua}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"PROHIBICI\u00d3N VENTA DE LICOR A MENORES DE DIECIOCHO A\u00d1OS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nicasalud.org.ni/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/CODIGO-DE-LA-NI%C3%91EZ-ADOLESCENCIA-Y-LA-FAMILIA-2014.pdf|title=C\u00d3DIGO DE LA NI\u00d1EZ Y LA ADOLESCENCIA. LEY No. 287|last=|first=|date=2014|website=|publisher=Asamblea Nacional de la Rep\u00fablica de Nicaragua|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref>\n| \n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Panama}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref>{{cite web|url=http://extwprlegs1.fao.org/docs/pdf/pan41786.pdf|title=EL CONSEJO NACIONAL DE LEGISLACION DECRETA: CAPITULO PRIMERO IMPUESTOS SOBRE EXPENDIO DE BEBIDAS ALCOHOLICAS.|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Consejo Nacional de Legislaci\u00f3n|accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Paraguay}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|20<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bacn.gov.py/leyes-paraguayas/5076/ley-n-1642-prohibe-la-venta-de-bebidas-alcoholicas-a-menores-de-edad-y-prohibe-su-consumo-en-la-via-publica|title=Ley N\u00b0 1.642 / 2000 - QUE PROH\u00cdBE LA VENTA DEBEBIDAS ALCOH\u00d3LICAS A MENORES DE EDAD Y PROH\u00cdBE SU CONSUMO EN LA V\u00cdA P\u00daBLICA|last=|first=|date=2016-06-13|website=|publisher=Biblioteca y Archivo Central del Congreso Nacional|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref>\n| \n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Peru}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref>{{cite web|url=https://docs.peru.justia.com/federales/leyes/28681-mar-3-2006.pdf |publisher=docs.peru.justia.com |title=Ley No. 28681 |accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | {{flag|Saint Kitts and Nevis}}\n|None\n|18\n|Liquor Licences Act Sec 32(f)\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" | {{flag|Saint Lucia}}\n|None\n|16\n|Chapter 13.17 Liquor Licence Act Art 37\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Saint Vincent and the Grenadines}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|16<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.who.int/substance_abuse/publications/global_alcohol_report/profiles/vct.pdf?ua=1|title=S a i n t Vi n c e n t a n d t h e G r e n a d i n e s|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|Chapter 342 Liquor License Act (1990), Sections 27 and 28\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Trinidad and Tobago}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Liquor Licenses Act Trinidad and Tobago\">{{cite web|url=http://rgd.legalaffairs.gov.tt/laws2/alphabetical_list/lawspdfs/84.10.pdf |title=Liquor Licenses Act - Section 60|accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell, serve or supply alcohol beverages to child under the age of 18 years. It is also prohibited for an adult to send a child to buy alcohol on behalf. It is not prohibited for children to buy or consume alcohol.<ref name=\"Liquor Licenses Act Trinidad and Tobago\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''{{flag|Turks and Caicos Islands}}''\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Liquor Licenses Act Turks and Caicos Islands\">{{cite web|url=http://online.fliphtml5.com/fizd/micd/#p=22 |title=Liquor Licenses Act - Section 27|accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to serve or sell liquor to a young person under the age of eighteen years. Minors under the age of sixteen years may not present in a licensed premises mainly serving and selling alcohol beverages.<ref name=\"Liquor Licenses Act Turks and Caicos Islands\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|United States}}<br />(50 states)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Varies by state<ref name=\"IARD\"/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |21<ref name=\"IARD\"/>\n| Some [[U. S. state|states]] do not allow those under the legal drinking age to be present in liquor stores or in [[bar (establishment)|bars]] (usually, the difference between a bar and a [[restaurant]] is that food is served only in the latter). Contrary to popular belief, only a few states prohibit [[minor (law)|minors]] and [[youth|young adults]] from consuming alcohol in private settings.\n\nThe National Institute on Alcohol Abuse and Alcoholism maintains a database that details state-level regulations on consumption and sale age limits.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://alcoholpolicy.niaaa.nih.gov/underage-drinking/state-profiles|title=APIS: State Profiles of Underage Drinking Laws|author=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=National Institute on Alcohol Abuse and Alcoholism|accessdate=2019-10-19}}</ref>\n\n{{See also|Minor in Possession|List of alcohol laws of the United States}}\n|-\n| United States\n|''{{flag|Puerto Rico}}''\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18\n|Law 118 Penalties for Provision of Alcoholic Beverages to Minors under 18 years of age (1984)\n|-\n| United States\n|''{{flag|United States Virgin Islands}}''\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vinow.com/general_usvi/faq/#drinking |title=Helpful Visitor Information for the Virgin Islands |publisher=Vinow.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-11}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Uruguay}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elobservador.com.uy/legisladores-quieren-prohibir-que-menores-18-consuman-bebidas-alcoholicas-n1044893 |title=Legisladores quieren prohibir que menores de 18 consuman bebidas alcoh\u00f3licas|accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n| Only selling alcohol to minors under the age of 18 is prohibited, consumption and purchase by minors is not prohibited.\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Venezuela}}\n| align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"LEY N\u00b0 28681\">{{cite web|url=https://www.fundacionbengoa.org/lactancia/legal/LOPNA.pdf|title=Gaceta Oficial N\u00b0 5. 266 Extraordinario de fecha 2 de octubre de 1998: LEY ORG\u00c1NICA PARA LA PROTECCI\u00d3N DEL NI\u00d1O Y DEL ADOLESCENTE|last=|first=|date=|website=|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref>\n| \n|}\n\n==Asia==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:15%;\"| Country\n! colspan=2 style=\"width:30%;\"| [[De jure]]\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:40%;\"| Notes\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Drinking age\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Purchase age\n|-\n| {{flag|Afghanistan}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|Prohibited <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.refworld.org/pdfid/4c58395a2.pdf|title=Penal Code (1976), Art 349-352|author=|first=|date=|work=Refworld|accessdate=7 October 2019}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Bahrain}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|Age 21\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Bangladesh}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|Prohibited for Muslims\n| \n|-\n| {{flag|Bhutan}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|18<ref name=\"bhutan\">{{cite web|url=https://bhutan.eregulations.org/media/rules%20and%20reg-%20license.pdf|title=Rules And Regulations For Establishment And Operation Of Industrial And Commercial Ventures In Bhutan, 1995|date=|accessdate=2015-04-29}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Brunei}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |17 for private residence consumption, but prohibited for Muslims<ref name=\"IARD\"/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Prohibited<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|Non-Muslims over 17 years of age are allowed to import alcohol not to exceed maximum total volume 2 liters of liquor and 12 cans of beer at 330 ml for personal use, once in 48 hours. This alcohol must be \u201cstored and consumed at the place of residence of the importer\u201d and is \u201cnot to be given, transferred or sold to another person.\u201d.<ref name=\"IARD\"/>\n|-\n| {{flag|Cambodia}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|None\n|The Health Ministry drafted a law to regulate the sale and consumption of alcohol in June 2015, with emphasis on establishing a minimum legal purchase age of 21 and preventing underage drinking.\n\nThe draft law has not yet been enacted. http