um Umur 21 Tahun|work=CNN Indonesia|access-date=2017-09-05}}</ref>\n|Sale is prohibited in Banda Aceh and Papua<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|- \n| {{flag|Iran}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|Prohibited<ref name=\"IARD\"/>\n| There is a ban on alcohol, but religious minorities may purchase small amounts from shops owned by the same religious minority.<ref>http://www.who.int/substance_abuse/publications/policy_iran.pdf</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Iraq}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|Prohibited<ref name=\"Daily Mail\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/oct/23/iraqs-parliament-passes-law-banning-alcohol|title=Iraq's parliament passes law banning alcohol |date=2016-10-23 |accessdate=2018-05-05}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Israel}}\n| align=\"center\"| 18<ref>Law to control alcohol intoxication (2010)</ref>\n| align=\"center\"| 18<ref name=\"IARD\"/>\n| Israel law prohibits selling or serving alcohol to minors. Minors are prohibited to drink alcohol in public places and the police may confiscate alcohol drinks from them.\n|-\n| {{flag|Japan}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|20<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elaws.e-gov.go.jp/search/elawsSearch/elaws_search/lsg0500/detail?lawId=211AC0000000020|title=Underage Drinking Prohibition Law (Act No. 20 of Taisho 11)|last=|first=|date=|website=e-gov Japan|access-date=2019-10-18}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Jordan}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18\n|Instructions issued by the Ministry of Interior Concerning Liquor Store Permits (2010), Article 6\n|-\n| {{flag|Kazakhstan}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | None\n|21\n|Law 235 of 2014 Code of Administrative Offences Section 200\n|-\n| {{flag|Kuwait}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|Prohibited<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|Law No. 46 (1964)\n|-\n| {{flag|Kyrgyzstan}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|18<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|Law No.269 Government Regulation of the Production and Sale of Alcohol (2009), Article 13.2\n|-\n| {{flag|Lebanon}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|18<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|Penal Code (1943), Articles 625-626 (promulgated by Legislative Decree No. 340 (2011) \nAccording to a global school health study, 40% of minors over 13 drink alcohol and up to 25% buy it from stores.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.executive-magazine.com/economics-policy/lebanons-underage-drinking-problem|title=Lebanon's underage drinking problem - Executive Magazine|date=2013-03-14|website=Executive Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-19}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''{{flag|Macau}}''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=2|None<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Malaysia}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|Sale to Muslims is prohibited; \n21 for others <ref name=\"IARD\" />\n| Food Act 1983 Food Regulations (1985) Regulation 361 (2014) and Food (Amendment) Regulations 2016 \nIncreased from 18 to 21 in December 2017, effective October 16, 2018. There will be an 18-month grace period for sellers to comply. After the grace period, anyone caught selling to persons under 21 can be fined up to RM10,000 and jailed up to 2 years.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/putrajaya-raises-legal-drinking-age-imposes-health-warnings |title=Putrajaya raises legal drinking age, imposes health warnings |author=Boo Su-Lyn |newspaper=Malay Mail Online |date=28 May 2016 |accessdate=7 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[Malaysian identity card]]<nowiki/>s include a designation of religion, which allows enforcement of the religion-based sales restriction.\n|-\n| {{flag|Maldives}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=2|Sale to citizens is prohibited;\n18 for tourists <ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|Sale of alcohol is limited to tourist resorts. It is prohibited to sell alcohol to local Maldivians<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mainlymaldives.co.uk/alcohol-maldives |work=MainlyMaldives.co.uk |title=Alcohol in the Maldives |date=5 December 2013 |accessdate=7 June 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Mongolia}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |21 / 18 with parent consent <ref name=\"who_mongolia\">[https://www.legalinfo.mn/law/showPrint/55 Law to Combat Alcoholism (2000)]</ref>\n|21<ref name=\"who_mongolia\" />\n|Those under 21 are prohibited from drinking alcohol; parents and guardians are prohibited from supplying alcohol to those under 18.\n|-\n| {{flag|Myanmar}}\n| align=\"center\"|None\n| align=\"center\"|18\n|Child Law (1993) Art 65\n\nExcise Act (1958) Art 40(7)\n|-\n| {{flag|Nepal}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|18<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lawcommission.gov.np/np/archives/category/documents/prevailing-law/statutes-acts/%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%8B%E0%A4%9F%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B2-%E0%A4%B5%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A5%E0%A4%BE-%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%A5%E0%A4%BE-%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE|title=Hotel Distribution and Wine Sales Distribution (Control) Act|last=|first=|date=|website=Nepal Law Commission|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref>\n|A policy has reportedly been adopted that would make the legal purchase age 21. However, there are exceptions to underage consumption for purposes of religious ceremonies.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nepal|url=https://iogt.org/news/2017/02/22/nepal-government-adopted-new-alcohol-law/ |publisher=[[IOGT International]] |accessdate=17 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|North Korea}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.drinkingmap.com/drinking-age-in-north-korea.html|title=Drinking Age in North Korea|publisher=|accessdate=28 July 2015}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Oman}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|21 <ref name=\"IARD\" />\n| Residents need personal liquor licenses to consume alcohol in their private residences.<ref name=\"FCO Oman\">{{cite web |title=Oman|url=https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/oman/local-laws-and-customs |publisher=[[Foreign and Commonwealth Office]] |accessdate=24 September 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Pakistan}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|Prohibited<ref name=\"IARD\"/>\n| Prohibition (Enforcement of Hadd) Order of February 19, 1979\nNon-Muslim citizens may possess alcohol to be used in accordance with religious ceremonies<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|-\n| {{flag|Palestinian Authority}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|16{{Citation needed|date=June 2016}}\n| Legal in most cities.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n|-\n| {{flag|Philippines}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | None\n|18\n|Minors (defined as under 18 years old) are prohibited to purchase alcohol and adults are prohibited to purchase or provide alcohol to minors. Minors are not prohibited to consume alcohol. ''Act Regulating the Access of Minors to Alcohol Section 4''\n|-\n| {{flag|Qatar}}\n| align=\"center\" |21\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=2|21{{Cite web|url=https://www.tripsavvy.com/legal-drinking-age-in-asia-3149734}}\n|The sale and consumption of alcohol beverages are not permitted in Qatar: Law No. 11 (2004), Article 272.\nForeigners holding valid residence permits can apply for licenses to purchase alcohol beverages from the Qatar Distribution Company.\n|-\n| {{flag|Saudi Arabia}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|Prohibited<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n| Drinking or possessing alcohol is prohibited in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. Persons who drink or possess alcohol are subject to arrest and trial. Punishments range from heavy fines, lengthy prison terms and whippings.{{Citation needed|date=June 2016}}\n|-\n| {{flag|Singapore}}\n| align=\"left\"|None <ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://sso.agc.gov.sg/Act/LCSCA2015|title=Liquor Control (Supply and Consumption) Act 2015|last=|first=|date=|website=Singapore Statutes Online|access-date=2019-10-18}}</ref> \n(18 at licensed premises)\n| align=\"center\"|18<ref name=\":3\" />\n\n|It is prohibited to sell alcohol to minors. Anyone caught selling, furnishing or acquiring alcohol in any licensed premise to persons below 18 can be fined up to $10,000.\n\nIt is also prohibited for minors to purchase, or attempt to purchase alcohol from any licensed premises, in which the minors can also be fined up to $10,000. However, the authorities rarely enforced this on minors.\n\nIt is technically legal for minors to possess and consume alcohol at home and in public (not in any licensed premises) as there is no law prohibiting it. It is also technically legal for someone to purchase alcohol and pass it to minors outside the store or licensed premise.<ref name=\":3\" />\n|-\n| {{flag|South Korea}}\n| align=\"center\"|None\n| align=\"center\"|19<ref name=\"law.go.kr\">http://www.law.go.kr/\ubc95\ub839/\uccad\uc18c\ub144\ubcf4\ud638\ubc95</ref>\n|The age limit for alcohol is after January 1 of the year one's age turns to 19.<ref name=\"law.go.kr\"/>\n|-\n| {{flag|Sri Lanka}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|21<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nddcb.gov.lk/Docs/acts/NATA%20Act%20English.pdf|title=NATIONAL AUTHORITY ON TOBACCO AND ALCOHOL ACT, No. 27 OF 2006|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Syria}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|None{{Citation needed|date=February 2013}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Taiwan}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |18\n|18<ref>[https://law.moj.gov.tw/ENG/LawClass/LawAll.aspx?pcode=D0050001 Protection of Children and Youth Welfare and Rights Act] (zh:\u5152\u7ae5\u53ca\u5c11\u5e74\u798f\u5229\u6cd5) of the Republic of China; Article 2 of defines children and youth as people under the age of 18.</ref>\n|Parents, guardians, and others taking care of people under 18 shall not supply alcohol to them or risk administrative fines of 10000 to 50000 [[new Taiwan dollar]]s (Art 55).\n\nNo person shall supply alcohol to anyone under the age of 18 (Art 91).\n|-\n| {{flag|Tajikistan}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None / 20\n|18<ref name=\"IARD\" /> \n|Sale to minors under 18 years old is prohibited by Article 12 of Law No. 451 on State Regulation of Production and Turnover of Ethyl Alcohol and Alcohol Products.{{Citation needed|date=February 2013}}\n\nParents are required to forbid their children who have not reached age 20 to consume alcohol beverages.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mfa.tj/ru/main/view/3958/zakon-respubliki-tadzhikistan-ob-otvetstvennosti-roditelei-za-obuchenie-i-vospitanie-detei|title=\u0417\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d \u0420\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u0422\u0430\u0434\u0436\u0438\u043a\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d \u043e\u0431 \u043e\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0440\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0439 \u0437\u0430 \u043e\u0431\u0443\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0438 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043f\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0434\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0439|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Thailand}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|20<ref name=\"Thai_drinking\" /> \n| The Alcoholic Beverage Control Act of 2008 increased the drinking age in Thailand from 18 to 20, private drinking is not regulated in private locations.<ref name=\"Thai_drinking\">{{cite web |last=Patin |first=Jennifer |title=Thailand Tourist Information: A Guide to Laws in Thailand |url=http://www.thailawforum.com/tourst-guide-laws-Thailand.html |publisher=Thailand Law Forum |accessdate=2013-01-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thaihealth.or.th/Content/25907-%E0%B8%95%E0%B9%88%E0%B8%B3%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%A7%E0%B9%88%E0%B8%B2%2020%20%E0%B8%9B%E0%B8%B5%20%E0%B9%84%E0%B8%A1%E0%B9%88%E0%B8%82%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A2%E0%B8%AA%E0%B8%B8%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%B2%E0%B9%83%E0%B8%AB%E0%B9%89.html|title=\u0e15\u0e48\u0e33\u0e01\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32 20 \u0e1b\u0e35 \u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e02\u0e32\u0e22\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e32\u0e43\u0e2b\u0e49|work=Thaihealth.or.th|accessdate=28 July 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Turkmenistan}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n|21\n|Law on Prevention of the Harmful Impact of Alcohol 2018 Art 22 prohibits sale to anyone below age 21.\n|-\n| {{flag|United Arab Emirates}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Varies by jurisdiction\nProhibited in Sharjah<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/united-arab-emirates/local-laws-and-customs|title=United Arab Emirates travel advice - GOVUK|website=www.gov.uk|access-date=2016-05-26}}</ref>\n|21\nProhibited for Muslims\n\nProhibited in Sharjah\n| Expatriate non-[[Muslim]] residents may request a liquor permit to purchase alcohol beverages, but it is prohibited for such holders to provide drinks to others.<ref name=\"Guidelines\">{{cite web |url=http://www.icap.org/PolicyIssues/DrinkingGuidelines/GuidelinesTable/tabid/204/Default.aspx |title=International Drinking Guidelines |publisher=[[International Center for Alcohol Policies]] |accessdate=2009-02-17}}</ref>\n\nThe legal age for drinking alcohol is 18 in Abu Dhabi (although a Ministry of Tourism by-law allows hotels to serve alcohol only to those over 21), and 21 in Dubai and the Northern Emirates (except Sharjah, where drinking alcohol is prohibited).<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIt is a punishable offence to drink, or to be under the influence of alcohol, in public.<ref name=\":0\" />\n|-\n| {{flag|Uzbekistan}}\n| align=\"center\"| None\n| align=\"center\"| 20 <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://lex.uz/ru/docs/1880047|title=\u2116\u0417\u0420\u0423-302 05.10.2011 \u0417\u0410\u041a\u041e\u041d \u0420\u0415\u0421\u041f\u0423\u0411\u041b\u0418\u041a\u0418 \u0423\u0417\u0411\u0415\u041a\u0418\u0421\u0422\u0410\u041d \u041e\u0411 \u041e\u0413\u0420\u0410\u041d\u0418\u0427\u0415\u041d\u0418\u0418 \u0420\u0410\u0421\u041f\u0420\u041e\u0421\u0422\u0420\u0410\u041d\u0415\u041d\u0418\u042f \u0418 \u0423\u041f\u041e\u0422\u0420\u0415\u0411\u041b\u0415\u041d\u0418\u042f \u0410\u041b\u041a\u041e\u0413\u041e\u041b\u042c\u041d\u041e\u0419 \u0418 \u0422\u0410\u0411\u0410\u0427\u041d\u041e\u0419 \u041f\u0420\u041e\u0414\u0423\u041a\u0426\u0418\u0418|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Vietnam}}\n| align=\"center\" | None\n|18<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|Decree 94/2012/ND-CP on Liquor Production and Trading (2012), Article 19.7\n|-\n| {{flag|Yemen}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=2|Prohibited{{Citation needed|date=August 2011}}\n|Exception is in [[Aden]] Region where it's legal for 21 and up{{Citation needed|date=June 2016}}\n|}\n\n==Europe==\n[[File:Drinking age Europe.svg|thumb|500px|'''Minimum legal age to purchase alcohol by country (2015):'''<br />{{legend|#FF0000|Minimum purchase age of 20 years}}{{legend|#0026FF|Minimum purchase age of 18 years}}{{legend|#00FFDD|Minimum purchase age of 17 years}}{{legend|#267F00|Minimum purchase age of 16 years}}|alt=]]\n[[File:Konsumverbot.svg|thumb|500px|'''Laws banning minors from consuming alcohol in public/private:'''<br />{{legend|#FF0000|Minimum age to consume alcohol in public and private}}{{legend|#FFD800|Minimum age to consume alcohol in public}}{{legend|#267F00|No minimum age to consume alcohol in public or private}}]]\nMost countries in [[Europe]] have set 18 as the minimum age to purchase alcohol. Although [[Austria]], [[Belgium]], [[Cyprus]], [[Denmark]], [[Germany]], [[Gibraltar]], [[Liechtenstein]], [[Luxembourg]], [[Malta]], [[Serbia]] and [[Switzerland]] (except [[Ticino]]) maintain a minimum purchase age below 18 years permitting minors either full or limited access to alcohol. In 2005,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.rp-online.de/politik/deutschland/eu-will-alkoholkauf-erst-ab-18-erlauben-aid-1.1607191 |title=EU will Alkoholkauf erst ab 18 erlauben |author=AFP, dpa |date=26 February 2005 |language=de |website=www.rp-online.de |access-date=23 March 2018}}</ref> 2007<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.abendblatt.de/politik/europa/article107217172/Die-EU-will-Alkohol-erst-ab-18-Jahren-freigeben.html |title=Die EU will Alkohol erst ab 18 Jahren freigeben |author=AFP, dpa |date=13 March 2007 |language=de |website=www.abendblatt.de |access-date=23 March 2018}}</ref> and 2015<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.welt.de/politik/ausland/article140181484/EU-Parlament-will-Alkohol-unter-18-verbieten.html |title=EU-Parlament will Alkohol unter 18 verbieten |author=Christoph B. Schiltz |date=27 April 2015 |language=de |website=www.welt.de/politik |access-date=23 March 2018}}</ref> harmonization at the [[European Union]] level toward a minimum purchase age of 18 was discussed, but not agreed.\n\nTimeline of changes to drinking/purchase age or laws restricting the access to alcohol for minors:\n\n* In 2002 the Spanish autonomous communities [[Madrid]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elinconformistadigital.com/modules.php?op=modload&name=News&file=article&sid=56 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20150408124810/http://www.elinconformistadigital.com/modules.php?op=modload&name=News&file=article&sid=56 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2015-04-08 |title=La ley seca aprobada en Madrid |author=Marlowe |date=2002-03-07 |language=es |website=elinconformistadigital.com |access-date=2015-04-07 }}</ref> [[Valencia]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.joves.net/estas-d-acord/augmentar-l-edat-per-a-consumir-alcohol |title=El Conseller Blasco propone aumentar la edad legal para el consumo de alcohol |date=2002 |language=es |website=joves.net |access-date=2015-04-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414042742/http://www.joves.net/estas-d-acord/augmentar-l-edat-per-a-consumir-alcohol |archivedate=2015-04-14 }}</ref> and [[Catalonia]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lasdrogas.info/noticias/453/cataluna-eleva-hasta-los-18-anos-la-edad-minima-para-poder-comprar-alcohol.html |title=Catalu\u00f1a eleva hasta los 18 a\u00f1os la edad m\u00ednima para poder comprar alcohol |date=2002-02-28 |language=es |website=lasdrogas.info |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref> raised their minimum purchase age to 18 years. Previously, Valencia and Madrid had a minimum purchase age of 16 years, and in Catalonia minors aged 16 or 17 could purchase alcohol up to 23% ABV on- and off-premise.\n* In 2004 [[Denmark]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.si-folkesundhed.dk/Ugens%20tal%20for%20folkesundhed/Ugens%20tal/Uge_12_2006.aspx |title=Forbud mod salg af alkohol til personer under 16 \u00e5r \u2013 virker det? |date=2006 |language=Danish|website=si-folkesundhed.dk |page=K\u00f8benhavn: Statens Institut for Folkesundhed |publisher=J\u00f8rgensen MH, Riegels M, Hesse U & Gr\u00f8nb\u00e6k M. |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref> raised its off-premise purchase age from 15 to 16 years.\n* In November 2005 Switzerland passed its Food and Commodities Regulation<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/20050153/index.html#a11 |title=Lebensmittel- und Gebrauchsgegenst\u00e4ndeverordnung - Art. 11 |language=de |website=admin.ch |publisher=The Federal Authorities of the Swiss Confederation |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref> (German: Lebensmittel- und Gebrauchsgegenst\u00e4ndeverordnung), introducing a ban on alcohol sales to anyone under the age of 16. The Alcohol Law<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/19320035/index.html#a41 |title=Bundesgesetz \u00fcber die gebrannten Wasser - Art. 41 |language=de |website=admin.ch |publisher=The Federal Authorities of the Swiss Confederation |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref> (German: Alkoholgesetz) passed in 1980 requires a minimum age of 18 years for the retail sale of distilled spirits. Therefore, it is prohibited to sell fermented alcohol (e.g. [[beer]], [[wine]], [[sparkling wine]] or [[cider]]) to anyone under the age of 16, and any distilled alcohol beverages to anyone under the age of 18 years. The canton of Ticino has a cantonal law since 1989 that makes the purchase age limit for all alcohol beverages 18 years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www3.ti.ch/CAN/RLeggi/public/raccolta-leggi/legge/numero/6.1.1.1 |title=Legge sulla promozione della salute e il coordinamento sanitario (Legge sanitaria) - Art. 51 |language=it |website=ti.ch |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref>\n* In 2006 the Spanish autonomous community [[Castile and Le\u00f3n]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elconfidencial.com/ultima-hora-en-vivo/2012/07/legislacion-contra-botellon-manos-comunidades-autonomas-20120728-2508.html |title=La legislaci\u00f3n contra el botell\u00f3n en manos de las comunidades aut\u00f3nomas |date=2012 |language=es |website=ElConfidencial.com |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref> raised its minimum purchase age from 16 to 18 years.\n* In late 2006, [[Gibraltar]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gibraltarlaws.gov.gi/articles/2006-11o.pdf |title=Children and Young Persons (Alcohol, Tobacco and Gaming) Act 2006 |date=2006 |website=gibraltarlaws.gov.gi |publisher=Government of Gibraltar |access-date=2015-04-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721031927/http://www.gibraltarlaws.gov.gi/articles/2006-11o.pdf |archive-date=2011-07-21 |url-status=dead }}</ref> lawmakers passed the ''Children and Young Persons (Alcohol, Tobacco and Gaming) Act 2006'', which raised the minimum purchase age from 16 to 18 years. But the new law made an exception: minors aged 16 or 17 can purchase and consume beer, wine or cider under 15% ABV on-premise, and pre-packed containers of an alcohol strength not exceeding 5.5% ABV (e.g. [[alcopops]]).\n* In 2009 [[France]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/actualite-france/2009/03/09/01016-20090309ARTFIG00563-les-deputes-interdisent-la-vente-d-alcool-aux-mineurs-.php |title=La vente d'alcool et de tabac interdite aux mineurs |author=Bastien Hugues |date=2009-03-09 |language=fr |website=lefigaro.fr |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref> raised its minimum purchase age to 18 years,<ref name=\"SantePublique3\">[http://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexteArticle.do;jsessionid=18ED9AC9EF67D77F5A2C0373B8E6B783.tpdjo08v_1?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000020879475&idArticle=LEGIARTI000020881176&dateTexte=20090920&categorieLien=id Law passed on 23 July 2009].</ref><ref name=\"SantePublique4\">[http://legifrance.gouv.fr/affichCodeArticle.do;jsessionid=EEA97DD8289FBEA8B0F379B642F59F2C.tpdjo10v_3?idArticle=LEGIARTI000006688129&cidTexte=LEGITEXT000006072665&dateTexte=20090722 French Public Health Code, Art L3353-4].</ref> and fines were increased for selling or serving alcohol to a minor (up to 7,500 \u20ac). Previously, the minimum age was 16 years for off-premise and on-premise purchases of low-alcohol beverages (up to 3% ABV) such as wine, beer, cider, perry, mead, cr\u00e8me de cassis and juices from fermented fruits or vegetables that contain 1.2 to 3\u00b0 alcohol, natural sweet wines from controlled cultivation and 18 for higher-ABV beverges.\n* In October 2009, the government of [[Malta]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://livinginmalta.com/miscellaneuos/legal-drinking-age/ |title=Legal Drinking Age |author=Mark |date=2014-06-16 |website=livinginmalta.com |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref> passed a new law raising its drinking and purchase age from 16 to 17 years.\n* In 2010 the Spanish autonomous community of [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]] raised its minimum purchase age from 16 to 18 years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2010/06/17/espana/1276794476.html |title=Galicia elevar\u00e1 de 16 a 18 a\u00f1os la edad para beber y multar\u00e1 la venta a menores |author=Santiago de Compostela |date=2010-06-17 |language=es |website=elmundo.es |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref>\n* In 2011 [[Denmark]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sundhedsstyrelsen.dk/da/sundhed/alkohol/lovgivning |title=Lovgivning p\u00e5 alkoholomr\u00e5det |date=2014-01-22 |language=Danish|website=sundhedsstyrelsen.dk |publisher=Sundhedsstyrelsen |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref> passed a law raising the minimum age for off-premise sale of alcohol beverages of >16.5% ABV to 18 years of age. The minimum age to purchase alcohol beverages of <16.5% ABV remains 16.\n* In March 2012 [[Moldova]] raised the minimum purchase age to 18, from 16 previously.<ref name=\"Art. 30\">[Art.30 lit.j) \u00een redac\u0163ia LP22 din 01.03.12, MO92/15.05.12 art.290]</ref><ref name=\"LEGE Nr. 1100\" />\n*[[Italy]] raised its minimum purchase age from 16 to 18 in 2012. Previously Italy did not have a purchase age for off-premise sales, and the minimum age of 16 years for on-premise sales was not well enforced.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ufficiocommercio.it/pf/testo-news/27926/Divieto-di-vendita-alcolici-ai-minori-di-anni-18 |title=Divieto di vendita alcolici ai minori di anni 18 |date=2012-11-14 |language=it |website=ufficiocommercio.it |publisher=Ufficio Commercio |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref>\n* In 2013 the government of [[Portugal]] restricted alcohol sales to young people: distilled spirits cannot be sold to anyone under the age of 18, and other alcohol beverages (e.g. beer, wine, or cider) cannot be sold to anyone under the age of 16. Previously the minimum age for all alcohol beverages was 16 years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ivv.min-agricultura.pt/np4/154?newsId=5684&fileName=NI_02_2013__27_05_2013_.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131107013535/http://www.ivv.min-agricultura.pt/np4/154?newsId=5684&fileName=NI_02_2013__27_05_2013_.pdf |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-11-07 |title=RESTRI\u00c7\u00d5ES \u00c0 DISPONIBILIZA\u00c7\u00c3O, VENDA E CONSUMO DE BEBIDAS ALCO\u00d3LICAS - N.\u00ba02/2013 |author=Instituto da Vinha e do Vinho |date=2013-03-27 |language=pt |website=ivv.min-agricultura.pt |access-date=2015-04-07 }}</ref>\n*{{As of|2014|January|1|df=UK}}, the minimum legal purchase and consumption age was raised from 16 to 18 in the [[Netherlands]]. Previously young people over the age of 16 could purchase and consume alcohol beverages of <15% ABV, and those aged 18 and over could purchase all alcohol beverages.<ref name=\"Alcohol in de wet\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rijksoverheid.nl/onderwerpen/alcohol/alcohol-in-de-wet |title=Alcohol in de wet |language=nl |website=rijksoverheid.nl |access-date=7 April 2015}}</ref>\n*{{As of|2015|March|df=UK}}, the Spanish autonomous community of [[Asturias]] raised its drinking age from 16 to 18 years. Asturias was Spain's last community with a drinking age of 16 years. The new law brings the drinking age into line with the rest of Spain, with the exception of Baleares Islands where no purchase age limit is set.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lne.es/asturias/2015/03/06/copas-saldran-caras-menores/1722639.html |title=Las copas saldr\u00e1n caras a los menores |date=2015-03-06 |language=es |website=lne.es |access-date=2015-04-07}}</ref>\n*{{As of|2015|December|df=UK}}, [[Portugal]] harmonized its minimum drinking age to 18 years across all beverage types. Previously the purchase age was 16 years for low-alcohol beverages such as beer, wine or cider.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://dre.pt/web/guest/legislacao-consolidada/-/lc/67421695/201704201944/exportPdf/normal/1/cacheLevelPage?_LegislacaoConsolidada_WAR_drefrontofficeportlet_rp=indice |title=Decreto-Lei n.\u00ba 50/2013 - Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica n.\u00ba 74/2013, S\u00e9rie I de 2013-04-16 [Amendment by Decreto-Lei n.\u00ba 106/2015 - Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica n.\u00ba 115/2015, S\u00e9rie I de 2015-06-16, em vigor a partir de 2015-07-01] |language=pt |website=dre.pt |access-date=24 July 2019}}</ref>\n*{{As of|2018|January|1|df=UK}}, [[Lithuania]] raised its minimum drinking age from 18 to 20 years.<ref name=\"Seimas adopted amendments on reduction of alcohol consumption\" />\n* From January 2019 the federal states of [[Austria]] decided to align their drinking and purchase ages. The states [[Burgenland]], [[Lower Austria]] and [[Vienna]] therefore raised their age limits for alcohol beverages containing spirits to 18. Prior to 2019 these states had a general drinking and purchase age of 16 years.The sale and consumption of beer, wine and other fermented alcohol beverages is now prohibited to children and young people under the age of 16 years, and the sale and consumption of spirits to minors under the age of 18 years throughout Austria.<ref name=\"austria\">{{cite web|url=https://www.oesterreich.gv.at/themen/jugendliche/jugendrechte/3/Seite.1740250.html|title=\u00d6sterreichs digitales Amt: Rauchen und Alkohol|last=|first=|date=2019-01-04|website=|language=de|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:10%;\" | Country\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:10%;\" | Administrative division\n! colspan=\"4\" style=\"width:40%;\" |[[De jure]]\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:40%;\" | Notes\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20%;\" | Drinking age<ref name=\"Eyes On Age\">{{cite web|url=https://ec.europa.eu/health/sites/health/files/alcohol/docs/eyes_on_ages_report_en.pdf|title=EYES ON AGES - A research on alcohol age limit policies in European Member States. Legislation, enforcement and research. |publisher=Dutch Institute for Alcohol Policy (STAP), European Commission |author=drs. J. Mulder, J. de Greeff MSc|accessdate=28 July 2019}}</ref>\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20%;\" | Purchase age\n|-\n! style=\"width:5%;\" | Private\n! style=\"width:5%;\" | Public\n! style=\"width:5%;\" | On-premise\n! style=\"width:5%;\" | Off-premise\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Albania}}\n| style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n|18<ref name=\"albania\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ishp.gov.al/wp-content/uploads/2015/ligjet/Per-mbrojtjen-e-te-mitruve-nga-perdorimi-i-alkoolit.pdf|title=LIGJ Nr. 9518, dat\u00eb 18.4.2006 - P\u00cbR MBROJTJEN E T\u00cb MITURVE NGA P\u00cbRDORIMI I ALKOOLIT [Law 9518 for the protection of minors from the use of alcohol (2006)] Art 4|last=|first=|date=|website=ishp.gov.al|language=sq|access-date=24 July 2019}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"albania\" />\n| The sale of alcohol beverage in bars, restaurants or other licensed premises, as well as other points of sale, is prohibited to minors under the age of 18 years. Vendors and operators of licensed premises are required to post a clearly legible notice in A4 format stating \"Ndalohet shitja e alkoolit personave n\u00ebn 18 vje\u00e7\" (It is prohibited to sell alcohol beverages to people under 18 years). Consumption by those under age 18 in public places is prohibited.<ref name=\"albania\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Andorra}}\n| style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"andorra\" />\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref name=\"andorra\">{{cite web |url=http://www.policia.ad/documentacio/venda_consum_begudes.pdf |title=Reglament pel qual es regulen determinats aspectes de la venda i el consum de begudes alcoh\u00f2liques|language=ca |website=policia.ad |access-date=25 July 2019}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref name=\"andorra\" />\n| Selling, serving or supplying alcohol beverages is prohibited as well as public consumption of alcohol beverage by minors under the age of 18 years.<ref name=\"andorra\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Armenia}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"\u054e\u0531\u0550\u0549\u0531\u053f\u0531\u0546 \u053b\u0550\u0531\u054e\u0531\u053d\u0531\u053d\u054f\u0548\u0552\u0544\u0546\u0535\u0550\u053b \u054e\u0535\u0550\u0531\u0532\u0535\u0550\u0545\u0531\u053c \u0540\u0531\u0545\u0531\u054d\u054f\u0531\u0546\u053b \u0540\u0531\u0546\u0550\u0531\u054a\u0535\u054f\u0548\u0552\u0539\u0545\u0531\u0546 \u0555\u0550\u0535\u0546\u054d\u0533\u053b\u0550\u0554\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"\u054e\u0531\u0550\u0549\u0531\u053f\u0531\u0546 \u053b\u0550\u0531\u054e\u0531\u053d\u0531\u053d\u054f\u0548\u0552\u0544\u0546\u0535\u0550\u053b \u054e\u0535\u0550\u0531\u0532\u0535\u0550\u0545\u0531\u053c \u0540\u0531\u0545\u0531\u054d\u054f\u0531\u0546\u053b \u0540\u0531\u0546\u0550\u0531\u054a\u0535\u054f\u0548\u0552\u0539\u0545\u0531\u0546 \u0555\u0550\u0535\u0546\u054d\u0533\u053b\u0550\u0554\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.am/legislation.php?sel=show&ID=1392&lang=arm|title=CODE OF THE REPUBLIC OF ARMENIA ON ADMINISTRATIVE VIOLATIONS|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=National Assembly|accessdate=7 October 2019|df=}}</ref>\n| There are no laws mandating alcohol vendors to ID potential underage drinkers. ID checks are very rarely, if ever, carried out<ref name=\"\u054e\u0531\u0550\u0549\u0531\u053f\u0531\u0546 \u053b\u0550\u0531\u054e\u0531\u053d\u0531\u053d\u054f\u0548\u0552\u0544\u0546\u0535\u0550\u053b \u054e\u0535\u0550\u0531\u0532\u0535\u0550\u0545\u0531\u053c \u0540\u0531\u0545\u0531\u054d\u054f\u0531\u0546\u053b \u0540\u0531\u0546\u0550\u0531\u054a\u0535\u054f\u0548\u0552\u0539\u0545\u0531\u0546 \u0555\u0550\u0535\u0546\u054d\u0533\u053b\u0550\u0554\" /> Criminal Code the Republic of Armenia (2003), Article 166: \"Involvement, by a person who reached 18 years, of a child into regular use of alcohol drinks... is punished with correctional labor for up to 1 year, or with arrest for the term of 1-2 months, or with imprisonment for the term of 5 years\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Austria}}\n| style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"austria\" />\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |16 <sup>(beer, wine and cider)</sup><br />18 <sup>([[distilled beverage]]s)</sup><ref name=\"austria\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |16 <sup>(beer, wine and cider)</sup><br />18 <sup>(distilled beverages)</sup><ref name=\"austria\" />\n| The age limits are set out by the legislation of each federal state but where harmonized in January 2019.<ref name=\"austria\" /> Carinthia also requires16-18-year-olds to maintain a blood alcohol level below 0.05%.<ref name=\"Rauchen und Alkohol\">[https://www.help.gv.at/Portal.Node/hlpd/public/content/174/Seite.1740250.html Rauchen und Alkohol] State legilations</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Azerbaijan}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Sosium \u2013 Siqaret qada\u011fas\u0131 g\u00fcnd\u0259md\u0259\">{{cite web|url=http://archive.bakupost.az/sosium/20131002094909678.html|title=Sosium \u2013 Siqaret qada\u011fas\u0131 g\u00fcnd\u0259md\u0259|publisher=bakupost.az|accessdate=22 March 2018|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103171132/http://archive.bakupost.az/sosium/20131002094909678.html|archivedate=3 January 2015}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Sosium \u2013 Siqaret qada\u011fas\u0131 g\u00fcnd\u0259md\u0259\" />\n| Law No. 499-IG on Children's Rights (1998)\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Belarus}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"\u041c\u0423\u0421 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0456 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0430\u043d\u0443\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0446\u044c \u043a\u0443\u0440\u044d\u043d\u043d\u0435 \u0456 \u045e\u0436\u044b\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0435 \u0430\u043b\u043a\u0430\u0433\u043e\u043b\u044e \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0430\u0441\u043e\u0431, \u043c\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0437\u0435\u0439\u0448\u044b\u0445 \u0437\u0430 18 \u0433\u0430\u0434\u043e\u045e\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pravo.by/document/?guid=3871&p0=h10800429|title=\u0417\u0410\u041a\u041e\u041d \u0420\u0415\u0421\u041f\u0423\u0411\u041b\u0418\u041a\u0418 \u0411\u0415\u041b\u0410\u0420\u0423\u0421\u042c 27 \u0430\u0432\u0433\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0430 2008 \u0433. \u2116 429-\u0417 \u041e \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u043c \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0443\u043b\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0437\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0438 \u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0430 \u0430\u043b\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439, \u043d\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0449\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u043f\u0438\u0440\u0442\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0449\u0435\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0443\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0438 \u043d\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0449\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0433\u043e \u044d\u0442\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0441\u043f\u0438\u0440\u0442\u0430|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=\u041d\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0435\u0442-\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b \u0420\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044c|accessdate=2019-10-21}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"\u041c\u0423\u0421 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0456 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0430\u043d\u0443\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0446\u044c \u043a\u0443\u0440\u044d\u043d\u043d\u0435 \u0456 \u045e\u0436\u044b\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0435 \u0430\u043b\u043a\u0430\u0433\u043e\u043b\u044e \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0430\u0441\u043e\u0431, \u043c\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0437\u0435\u0439\u0448\u044b\u0445 \u0437\u0430 18 \u0433\u0430\u0434\u043e\u045e\" />\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Belgium}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Vente et consommation d\u2019alcool en Belgique\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18 for distilled beverages of higher than 1.2%ABV and fermented beverages of higher than 22%ABV\n16 for other alcohol beverages<ref name=\"Vente et consommation d\u2019alcool en Belgique\">{{cite web|url=https://www.health.belgium.be/fr/sante/prenez-soin-de-vous/alcool-et-tabac/alcool|title=Alcool|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Service Public Federal|accessdate=2019-10-21}}</ref>\n| Since 10 January 2010, it is prohibited to \"sell, serve, or offer\" any distilled alcohol beverages to those under the age of 18 or any alcohol beverage to those under 16.<ref name=\"Vente et consommation d\u2019alcool en Belgique\" /> Previously, it was prohibited to sell alcohol drinks to under-16s, but accompanying adults could buy drinks for them.\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Bosnia and Herzegovina}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Drinking age Bosnia\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Drinking age Bosnia\">{{cite web |url=http://novi-informator.net/prodaja-alkoholnih-pi%C4%87-osobama-mla%C4%91im-od-18-godina |title=Prodaja alkoholnih pi\u0107a osobama mla\u0111im od 18 godina |publisher=jeunesetalcool.be |date= |accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n| Selling alcohol to a minor under the age of 18 years is an offence. The law does not prohibit minors from buying, attempting to buy or consuming alcohol.<ref name=\"Drinking age Bosnia\" />\n\n* Law on Public Peace and Order (2015) Article 25 prohibits providing alcohol beverages to minors.\n* Law on Internal Trade (2010), Article 10 prohibits the sale in the retail trade of alcohol beverages to persons under 18 years of age.\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Bulgaria}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"\u0414\u0435\u0446\u0430 \u0438 \u044e\u043d\u043e\u0448\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0434 18 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0438\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"\u0414\u0435\u0446\u0430 \u0438 \u044e\u043d\u043e\u0448\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0434 18 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0438\">{{cite web|url=https://www.lex.bg/laws/ldoc/2134925825|title=\u0417\u0410\u041a\u041e\u041d \u0417\u0410 \u0417\u0410\u041a\u0420\u0418\u041b\u0410 \u041d\u0410 \u0414\u0415\u0422\u0415\u0422\u041e|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Lex.bg|accessdate=2019-10-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lex.bg/bg/laws/ldoc/2135489147|title=\u0417\u0410\u041a\u041e\u041d \u0417\u0410 \u0417\u0414\u0420\u0410\u0412\u0415\u0422\u041e|last=|first=|date=|website=Lex.bg|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref>\n|It is prohibited to sell or offer alcohol beverages to any child under the age of 18.<ref name=\"\u0414\u0435\u0446\u0430 \u0438 \u044e\u043d\u043e\u0448\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0434 18 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0438\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Croatia}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Drinking age Croatia\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Drinking age Croatia\">{{cite web|url=https://www.zakon.hr/z/175/Zakon-o-trgovini|title=Zakon o trgovini|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=zakon.hr|accessdate=2019-10-24}}</ref>\n|It is prohibited to sell or serve alcohol to anyone under 18 years of age. There is no minimum age to buy or consume alcohol by law.<ref name=\"Drinking age Croatia\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Cyprus}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |17<ref name=\"Drinking age Cyprus\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cylaw.org/nomoi/enop/non-ind/0_144/full.html|title=\u039f \u03c0\u03b5\u03c1\u03af \u03a0\u03c9\u03bb\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03c2 \u039f\u03b9\u03bd\u03bf\u03c0\u03bd\u03b5\u03c5\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03b4\u03ce\u03bd \u03a0\u03bf\u03c4\u03ce\u03bd \u039d\u03cc\u03bc\u03bf\u03c2 (\u039a\u0395\u03a6.144)|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=CyLaw|accessdate=2019-10-24}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |17<ref name=\"Drinking age Cyprus\" />\n| It is prohibited to sell or serve alcohol to anyone under the age of 17 years, and for those under 17 years old to consume alcohol beverages.<ref name=\"Drinking age Cyprus\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Czechia}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\":6\" />\n| It is prohibited to provide alcohol to minors but consumption itself is not prohibited by law.<ref name=\":6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.zakonyprolidi.cz/cs/2017-65|title=Z\u00e1kon \u010d. 65/2017 Sb. Z\u00e1kon o ochran\u011b zdrav\u00ed p\u0159ed \u0161kodliv\u00fdmi \u00fa\u010dinky n\u00e1vykov\u00fdch l\u00e1tek|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|accessdate=2019-10-24}}</ref> \n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Denmark}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"dansk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.retsinformation.dk/Forms/R0710.aspx?id=210239|title=Bekendtg\u00f8relse af lov om forbud mod salg af tobak og alkohol til personer under 18 \u00e5r|first=|date=|website=|publisher=https://www.retsinformation.dk|language=da|accessdate=2019-10-24}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"dansk\" />\n| align=\"center\" |16 <sup>(beverages of <16.5% [[ABV]])</sup> <br /> 18 <sup>(beverages of \u226516.5% [[ABV]])</sup><ref name=\"dansk\" />\n| While there is no age requirement for drinking alcohol beverages in Denmark, there are laws that prohibit minors from buying alcohol from on-premise and off-premise outlets.\n\nIf a shop or bar fails to ask for an ID card and is identified having sold alcohol to an underage, it is subject to fine. A national ID card, obtained in the local town hall, can serve as age verification.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.retsinformation.dk/Forms/R0710.aspx?id=9878 |title=Lov om forbud mod salg af tobak og alkohol til personer under 16 \u00e5r |language=Danish|accessdate=2013-01-08}}</ref> This card is rarely used though since a passport or driver's license is more commonly used.<ref>[http://www.dr.dk/Nyheder/Indland/2006/07/01/.htm F\u00e5 unge har k\u00f8bt legitimationskort] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111127114344/http://www.dr.dk/Nyheder/Indland/2006/07/01/.htm |date=2011-11-27 }}, Danmarks Radio, 01. July 2006</ref>\n\nBoth the legal drinking and purchasing age in the Faroe Islands is 18.{{citation needed|date=October 2017}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Estonia}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref name=\"estonia\">{{cite web|url=https://www.riigiteataja.ee/akt/832173|title=Alkoholiseadus|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Riigi Teataja|accessdate=2019-10-24}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref name=\"estonia\" />\n| It is prohibited to sell, serve or supply alcohol beverages to anyone under the age of 18 years. Alcohol found in possession of any child can be confiscated by the police.\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Finland}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18 <sup>(1.2\u201322% ABV)</sup><br>20 <sup>(>22% ABV)</sup><ref name=\"alkoholilaki\">{{cite web|url=http://www.finlex.fi/fi/laki/ajantasa/1994/19941143|title=Alkoholilaki 1143/1994 - Ajantasainen lains\u00e4\u00e4d\u00e4nt\u00f6 - FINLEX \u00ae|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060430234325/http://www.finlex.fi/fi/laki/ajantasa/1994/19941143|archive-date=2006-04-30|accessdate=2019-10-24}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |18 <ref name=\"alkoholilaki\" />\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |18 <sup>(1.2\u201322% ABV)</sup><br>20 <sup>(>22% ABV)</sup><ref name=\"alkoholilaki\" />\n| All major grocery chains have implemented a policy to ask for ID if the customer looks under 30.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://yle.fi/uutiset/if_you_look_under_30_get_your_id_out/6333481|title=If you look under 30, get your ID out|publisher=YLE News|date=2012-10-12|accessdate=2013-04-21}}</ref> Stores may refuse to sell alcohol if the customer is accompanied by a minor, or if proxy purchasing is suspected.  Purchasing alcohol on behalf of a minor is a criminal offence.<ref name=\"alkoholilaki\" />\n\nPolice may search minors in public places and confiscate or destroy any alcohol beverages in their possession. Incidents are reported to the legal guardian and social authorities, who may intervene with child welfare procedures. In addition, those aged 15 or above are subject to a fine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.finlex.fi/fi/laki/ajantasa/2010/20100756#P17|title=Laki rikesakkorikkomuksista 756/2010 - Ajantasainen lains\u00e4\u00e4d\u00e4nt\u00f6 - FINLEX \u00ae|publisher=|accessdate=28 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn private, offering alcohol to a minor is considered a criminal offence if it results in drunkenness and the act can be deemed reprehensible as a whole, considering the minor's age, degree of maturity and other circumstances.<ref name=\"alkoholilaki\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|France}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"SantePublique2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichCodeArticle.do;jsessionid=18ED9AC9EF67D77F5A2C0373B8E6B783.tpdjo08v_1?cidTexte=LEGITEXT000006072665&idArticle=LEGIARTI000020895230&dateTexte=|title=Code de la sant\u00e9 publique - Article L3353-3|last=|first=|date=|website=Legifrance|publisher=|accessdate=2019-10-24}}</ref> \n|[[France]] has no explicitly stated consumption age, but selling alcohol beverages to a minor (under 18) is prohibited and can be fined 7500 [[euro]]s.<ref name=\"SantePublique2\" /> \n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Georgia|Georgia (country)}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Georgia\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Georgia\">{{cite book|url=https://matsne.gov.ge/ka/document/view/15652?publication=4|title=\u10d9\u10dd\u10dc\u10e1\u10dd\u10da\u10d8\u10d3\u10d8\u10e0\u10d4\u10d1\u10e3\u10da\u10d8 \u10d5\u10d4\u10e0\u10e1\u10d8\u10d0 (\u10e1\u10d0\u10d1\u10dd\u10da\u10dd\u10dd)|last=|first=|date=31 October 2008|publisher=|isbn=|location=|pages=|accessdate=2019-10-24}}</ref>\n| Under the Law on Protecting Minors from Harmful Influences 2001 the sale of alcohol beverages to minors is prohibited.<ref name=\"Georgia\" /> Juvenile Justice Code (2015) Article 3 defines minors as those under 18.\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Germany}}\n| style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |14<sup>(beer, wine and cider if accompanied)</sup><br />16 <sup>(beer, wine and cider)</sup><br />18 <sup>(spirits and foods containing spirits above negligible amounts)</sup><ref name=\"Germany\">{{cite book |url=http://www.bmfsfj.de/RedaktionBMFSFJ/Abteilung5/Pdf-Anlagen/jschg-englisch,property=pdf,bereich=bmfsfj,sprache=de,rwb=true.pdf |title=Protection of Young Persons Act, Amendment by Article 3, Act |date=31 October 2008 |accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |14<sup>(beer, wine and cider if accompanied)</sup><br />16 <sup>(beer, wine and cider)</sup><br />18 <sup>(spirits and foods containing spirits above negligible amounts)</sup><ref name=\"Germany\" />\n|It is prohibited to sell, serve or supply fermented alcohol beverages (beer, wine, cider and sparkling wine) to anyone under 16 years of age. However this age limit drops down to 14 if a minor is accompanied by his parent or legal guardian. It is generally prohibited to serve, sell or supply any beverage containing spirits and foods containing spirits above negligible amounts, to anyone under the age of 18 years. Violation of the \"Protection of Young Persons Act\" can be fined up to \u20ac50.000.<br />{{See also|Alcohol laws in Germany}}{{See also|Protection of Young Persons Act (Germany)}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Gibraltar}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Gibraltar\" />\n| align=\"center\" | 16 <sup>(beer, wine and cider)</sup><br />18 <sup>(spirits)</sup><ref name=\"Gibraltar\" />\n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"Gibraltar\" />\n| It is prohibited to sell alcohol drinks to anyone under the age of 18, other than the following two exceptions. The minimum age to be served in licensed premises is 16 if:<ref name=\"Gibraltar\">[http://www.gibraltarlaws.gov.gi/articles/2006-11o.pdf Children and Young Persons (Alcohol, Tobacco, and Gaming) Act 2006] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721031927/http://www.gibraltarlaws.gov.gi/articles/2006-11o.pdf |date=2011-07-21 }} (Gibraltar Laws).</ref>\n\n* The alcohol beverage is beer, wine or cider below 15% [[ABV]], '''or'''\n* The alcohol beverage is served in a bottle, or a pre-packaged container below 5.5% [[ABV]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Greece}}\n| style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"\u03a6\u0395\u039a A 262/2008\" />\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"\u03a6\u0395\u039a A 262/2008\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"\u03a6\u0395\u039a A 262/2008\">{{cite web|url=https://www.kodiko.gr/nomologia/document_navigation/141125/nomos-3730-2008|title=\u039d\u039f\u039c\u039f\u03a3 3730/2008 \u03a6\u0395\u039a \u039c\u03b5 \u03c4\u03b9\u03c2 \u03c4\u03b5\u03bb\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b1\u03af\u03b5\u03c2 \u03b1\u03bb\u03bb\u03b1\u03b3\u03ad\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf \u039d\u03cc\u03bc\u03bf 4633/2019|last=|first=|date=2008-12-23|website=Kodiko.gr|publisher=|access-date=2019-10-24}}</ref>\n| In 2008, the consumption of alcohol beverages was prohibited for minors in public. However, the law does not apply to private events or private premises.<ref name=\"\u03a6\u0395\u039a A 262/2008\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Hungary}}\n| style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Iceland}}\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |None\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |20<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.althingi.is/altext/stjt/1998.075.html|title=\u00c1fengisl\u00f6g|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2019-10-23}}</ref>\n| Possession or consumption of alcohol by people under the age of 20 is not an offence, but supplying them with alcohol is.\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Ireland}}\n| style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Ireland\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.citizensinformation.ie/en/reference/checklists/checklist_at_what_age_can_i.html|title=At what age can I?|website=www.citizensinformation.ie|language=en|access-date=2017-02-28}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Ireland\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Ireland\" />\n| It is prohibited for minors to buy alcohol or for a third party to attempt to buy it for minors. Minors are prohibited to drink in private residences unless it is with their parent or guardian's permission.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.citizensinformation.ie/en/justice/criminal_law/criminal_offences/alcohol_and_the_law.html |title=Alcohol and the law |publisher=Citizensinformation.ie |date=2012-03-07 |accessdate=2012-08-11}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Italy}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Trova Norme & Concorsi - Normativa Sanitaria\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.altalex.com/documents/leggi/2012/11/12/dl-sanita-la-legge-di-conversione-del-decreto-balduzzi|title=DL sanit\u00e0: La legge di conversione del decreto Balduzzi Legge, 08/11/2012 n\u00b0 189, G.U. 10/11/2012|last=|first=|date=|work=|accessdate=2019-10-23|publisher=Altalex}}</ref><ref name=\"Trova Norme & Concorsi - Normativa Sanitaria\" />\n| In 2012 the then Health Minister Renato Balduzzi proposed to raise the age to 18.<ref name=\"Trova Norme & Concorsi - Normativa Sanitaria\">{{cite web|url=http://www.trovanorme.salute.gov.it/norme/dettaglioAtto.spring?id=43801&completo=true|title=Trova Norme & Concorsi - Normativa Sanitaria|author=Istituto Poligrafico e Zecca dello Stato S.p.A.|publisher=|accessdate=28 July 2015}}</ref> Selling alcohol to those under the age of 18 in shops carries a fine between \u20ac250 and \u20ac1000. Serving alcohol beverages to those under the age of 16 is a criminal offense and is punished with prison up to one year, if the individual is 16 or 17 it will be treated as an offense that is fined between \u20ac250 and \u20ac1000 ''(Legge n. 189/2013)''.\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Kosovo}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |Unknown\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Latvia}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"Alkoholisko dz\u0113rienu aprites likums\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"Alkoholisko dz\u0113rienu aprites likums\">{{cite news|url=https://likumi.lv/ta/id/88009|title=Alkoholisko dz\u0113rienu aprites likums|last=|first=|date=May 1, 2004|work=|accessdate=2019-10-23|publisher=likumi.lv}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell or serve alcohol beverages to any minor under the age of 18 years.  Persons between the ages of 18 and 25 are required to present an identity document to the retailer when purchasing alcohoc beverages, regardless of whether the retailer has requested it. There is no minimum age to consume or possess alcohol.<ref name=\"Alkoholisko dz\u0113rienu aprites likums\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Liechtenstein}}\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |18 <sup>spirits and spirit-based beverages</sup>\n\n16 <sup>other alcohol beverages</sup> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gesetze.li/chrono/2009029000|title=Kinder- und Jugendgesetz (KJG) vom 10. Dezember 2008|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2019-10-23}}</ref>\n| Spirits and alcopops may be sold only to people at least 18, and other alcohol beverages to people at least 16. Consumption and possession is prohibited at the same ages. \n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Lithuania}}\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |20<ref name=\"Seimas adopted amendments on reduction of alcohol consumption\">{{cite news|url=https://www.e-tar.lt/portal/lt/legalAct/TAR.9E5C5C16B6E6/asr|title=Lietuvos Respublikos alkoholio kontrol\u0117s \u012fstatymas|last=|first=|date=|work=|accessdate=2019-10-23|publisher=e-tar.lt}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell, serve or supply alcohol beverages to anyone under the age of 20 years. People under the age of 20 are prohibited from consuming alcohol beverages or from possessing them. The minimum age was raised from 18 to 20 in 2018.<ref 