|18<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.paragraf.rs/propisi/zakon_o_zastiti_potrosaca.html|title=ZAKON O ZA\u0160TITI POTRO\u0160A\u010cA (\"Sl. glasnik RS\", br. 62/2014, 6/2016 - dr. zakon i 44/2018 - dr. zakon)|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Slovakia}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref name=\"slovakia\">{{cite web|url=https://www.zakonypreludi.sk/zz/1996-219|title=Z\u00e1kon \u010d. 219/1996 Z. z. o ochrane pred zneu\u017e\u00edvan\u00edm alkoholick\u00fdch n\u00e1pojov a o zria\u010fovan\u00ed a prev\u00e1dzke protialkoholick\u00fdch z\u00e1chytn\u00fdch izieb|last=|first=|date=|website=|accessdate=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref name=\"slovakia\" />\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Slovenia}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None<ref name=\"slovenia\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18<ref name=\"slovenia\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nalijem.si/o-alkoholu/alkohol-in-zakoni |title= Z\u00e1kon o ochrane pred zneu\u017e\u00edvan\u00edm alkoholick\u00fdch n\u00e1pojov a o zria\u010fovan\u00ed a prev\u00e1dzke protialkoholick\u00fdch z\u00e1chytn\u00fdch izieb |accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n| \n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Spain}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mscbs.gob.es/alcoholJovenes/legislacion/legislacionEstatal.htm|title=Alcohol and youth - Legislation|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Health, Social Services and Equality|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n|Autonomous region Islas Baleares does not have legislation on legal purchase age limits.\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Sweden}}\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"swe2010\" /><ref name=\"sweden\">{{cite web|url=https://vanligafragor.systembolaget.se/org/systembolaget/d/varfor-ar-det-18-arsgrans-pa-restaurang-och-krogen/|title=Systembolaget FAQ: Why is there an 18-year age limit on the pub but a 20-year age limit for Systembolaget?|last=|first=|date=|website=Systembolaget|publisher=Systembolaget.se|accessdate=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" |20<ref name=\"swe2010\" /> \n|{{See also|Alcohol in Sweden}}It is legal for anyone at any age to drink, but off-premise sale or supply to anyone under the age of 20 is prohibited and on-premise establishments are prohibited from serving alcohol beverages to anyone under 18. It is legal to serve an underage person alcohol in a private place, provided it's a limited amount and done in moderation.<ref name=\"swe2010\">{{cite web|url=https://www.riksdagen.se/sv/dokument-lagar/dokument/svensk-forfattningssamling/alkohollag-20101622_sfs-2010-1622|title=3 Kap. 7\u00a7 Alkohollag (2010:1622)|publisher=|accessdate=27 June 2018}}</ref> The reason for the lower limit in bars than in Systembolaget shops is that bartenders have a legal responsibility for how drunk a guest gets.<ref name=\"sweden\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Switzerland}}\n|{{flag|Switzerland}} (federal law)\n| colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |16 <sup>(fermented beverages with up to 15% ABV and natural wines with up to 18% ABV)</sup><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/20050153/index.html#a11 |title=817.02 Lebensmittel- und Gebrauchsgegenst\u00e4ndeverordnung Art. 11 |publisher=admin.ch |date= |accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref><br /> 18 <sup>(spirits)</sup><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/19320035/index.html#a41 |title=680 Bundesgesetz \u00fcber die gebrannten Wasser Art. 41 IV. 1. i. |publisher=admin.ch |date= |accessdate=2015-01-09}}</ref>\n| Whoever offers or supplies alcohol beverages to a child under the age of 16 years in an amount which is harmful to one's health is punished with imprisonment up to 3 years or a fine.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/19370083/201501010000/311.0.pdf |title=311.0 Schweizerisches Strafgesetzbuch vom 21. Dezember 1937 (Stand am 1. Januar 2015) - Art. 411 |author= |date= |language=de |website=admin.ch |page= |publisher=Swiss Federal Council |access-date=2015-08-09}}</ref> Whoever sells or supplies spirits to a person under the age of 18 years is punished with a fine up to 10.000 CHF.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/19320035/index.html#a57 |title=680 Bundesgesetz vom 21. Juni 1932 \u00fcber die gebrannten Wasser (Alkoholgesetz) - Art. 57 |author= |date= |language=de |website=admin.ch |page= |publisher=Swiss Federal Council |access-date=2015-08-09}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flag|Ticino}}\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |18\n| Canton [[Ticino]] prohibits the selling of any type of alcohol beverage to minors under the age of 18.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www3.ti.ch/CAN/RLeggi/public/index.php/raccolta-leggi/pdfatto/atto/628 |title=RL 942.100 Legge sugli esercizi alberghieri e sulla ristorazione del 1\u00b0 giugno 2010 (stato 15 giugno 2017) - art. 23 cpv. 1 lit. a |language=it |website=ti.ch |accessdate=2019-03-02}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Turkey}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |None\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mevzuat.gov.tr/MevzuatMetin/1.3.4250.pdf|title=\u0130SP\u0130RTO VE \u0130SP\u0130RTOLU \u0130\u00c7K\u0130LER \u0130NH\u0130SARI KANUNU|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n|{{See also|Alcohol laws of Turkey}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Ukraine}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |18<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|Law No. 1824-VI on state regulation of production and turnover of ethyl, cognac and fruit, alcoholic beverages and tobacco products Article 15-3\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |{{flag|United Kingdom}}\n|{{flag|England}} <br /> {{flag|Wales}}\n| align=\"center\" | None / 5<ref name=\"uk\" />\n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"uk\" /> 16 <sup>(beer, wine or cider with meal and if accompanied by adult)</sup><ref name=\"scotland\" />\n| align=\"center\" | 18 <ref name=\"uk\" /> \n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"uk\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2003/17/contents|title=Licensing Act 2003|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n|\n* It is prohibited to sell, serve, or offer alcohol beverages in licensed premises under the age of 18,<ref name=\"uk\" /> but minors aged 16\u201317 may consume wine, beer or cider on licensed premises when ordered with a meal and they are accompanied by an adult. Minors are prohibited to consume alcohol beverages in public.\n* Import: People over 17 are entitled to a duty-free allowance for alcohol beverages.\n|-\n|{{flag|Scotland}}\n| style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"scotland\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/alcohol-young-people-law|title=Alcohol and young people - GOV.UK|last=|first=|date=|website=www.gov.uk|accessdate=2019-10-22}}</ref> 16 <sup>(beer, wine or cider with meal if accompanied by adult))</sup><ref name=\"scotland\" />\n| align=\"center\" | 18\n| align=\"center\" | 18<ref name=\"scotland\" />\n|\n* It is prohibited to sell, serve, or offer alcohol beverages to anyone under the age of 18, but minors aged 16\u201317 may consume wine, beer or cider on licensed premises when ordered with a meal and they are accompanied by an adult. Minors are prohibited to consume alcohol beverages in public.<ref name=\"Licensing Act 2005\">{{cite web|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/asp/2005/16/part/8/crossheading/offences-relating-to-children-and-young-people|title=Licensing (Scotland) Act 2005|publisher=|accessdate=28 July 2015}}</ref>\n*Import: People over 17 are entitled to a duty-free allowance for alcohol beverages.<ref name=\"UK Duty Free\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/duty-free-goods/arrivals-from-outside-the-eu|title=Bringing goods into the UK - 3. Arrivals from outside the EU|website=gov.uk|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flag|Northern Ireland|union}}\n| style=\"background:Gainsboro\" align=\"center\" |None\n| align=\"center\" | 18\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | 18\n|It is prohibited to sell, serve, or offer alcohol beverages to anyone under the age of 18. Minors are prohibited to consume alcohol beverages in public.\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" |{{flag|United Kingdom}}\n|Under the [[British Beer and Pub Association|BBPA]]'s [[Challenge 21|Challenge 21 and Challenge 25]] schemes, customers attempting to buy alcohol beverages are asked to prove their age if in the retailer's opinion they look under 21<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beerandpub.com/industry-briefings/challenge-21|title=BBPA Home - Industry Briefings - Challenge 21|publisher=}}</ref> (or optionally 25) even though the law states they must be a minimum of 18. Many supermarket and off-licence chains display Challenge 21 (or Challenge 25) notices stating that they will not serve people who look under 21 (or 25) without ID.\n|}\n\n==Oceania==\n[[File:Alkoholersterwerbsalter in Ozeanien.png|thumb|230px|'''Minimum legal age to purchase alcohol by country (2015):'''<br />{{legend|#7F0000|Minimum purchase age of 21 years}}{{legend|#0026FF|Minimum purchase age of 18 years}}{{legend|#808080|No minimum purchase age}}|alt=]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:75%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:15%;\"| Country\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:15%;\"| State/region/province\n! colspan=2 style=\"width:30%;\"| [[De jure]]\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:40%;\"| Notes\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Drinking age\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Purchase age\n|-\n| United States\n|''{{flag|American Samoa}}''\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 21<ref>{{cite web|title=ALCOHOL REFORM ISSUES PAPER|url=http://www.samoalawreform.gov.ws/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Alcohol-Reform-Issues-Paper-Final.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140917184910/http://www.samoalawreform.gov.ws/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Alcohol-Reform-Issues-Paper-Final.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-date=17 September 2014|website=samoalawreform.gov.ws|publisher=Samoa Law Reform Commission|accessdate=25 March 2015}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Australia}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Varies by state.\n|18<ref name=\"IARD\" />\n|{{main|Alcohol laws of Australia}}All states restrict purchasing to over 18, but exceptions may apply if accompanied by a parent or guardian. The government-supported Youth Law Australia portal offers details on consumption and supply age limits by state.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://yla.org.au/nsw/topics/teen-issues/alcohol/|title=Teen issues: Alcohol|last=|first=|date=|website=Youth Law Australia|publisher=Department of Health Victoria|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Fiji}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 18<ref name=\"Fiji\">{{cite web|url=https://www.laws.gov.fj/Acts/DisplayAct/273|title=Liquor Act 2006|last=|first=|date=2018-08-01|website=|publisher=Fijitimes.com|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref>\n| The drinking age was previously 21 but was lowered to 18 in 2009.<ref name=\"Fiji\"/>\n|-\n| United States\n|''{{flag|Guam}}''\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | 18\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{flag|Micronesia, Federated States of}}\n| {{flag|Chuuk}} <br /> {{flag|Kosrae}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 18<ref>Draft Chuuk State Code (2012) Section 1307(1) - unenacted draft code citing source laws</ref><ref>Kosrae State Code (1997), Sections S.1.201(44) and 13.517(3)</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Pohnpei}} <br /> {{flag|Yap}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 21<ref>Code of the State of Pohnpei (2012), Section 2-109</ref><ref>Yap State Code (1987), Section 405</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|New Zealand}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| None || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 18<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alcohol.org.nz/management-laws/nz-alcohol-laws/sale-and-supply-of-alcohol-act-2012|title=Sale and Supply of Alcohol Act 2012|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=alcohol.org.nz|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref>\n| Minimum age applies for beverages with 1.15% ABV or over; no restrictions on beverages less than 1.15% ABV.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.legislation.govt.nz/act/public/1989/0063/latest/DLM165121.html#DLM165121 |title= 2 Interpretation -- Sale of Liquor Act 1989 No 63 (as at 01 July 2011), Public Act -- New Zealand Legislation Online |publisher=Parliamentary Counsel Office |date=1 July 2011 |accessdate=2013-01-08}}</ref><br>Persons under 18 may drink outside private residences or private functions if accompanied by their parent or legal guardian. Alcohol may be supplied to minors only by, or with express consent from, their parent or legal guardian.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://alcohol.org.nz/help-advice/advice-on-alcohol/for-parents/the-law-about-supply-to-young-people |title=The law about supply to young people |publisher=Alcohol.org.nz |accessdate=30 April 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| United States\n|''{{flag|Northern Mariana Islands}}''\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|21<ref name=\"Northern Mariana Islands Public Law 19-84\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cnmilaw.org/pdf/public_laws/19/pl19-84.pdf|title=H. B. No. 19-141 HDI SSI|publisher=cnmilaw.org|accessdate=22 March 2018}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| colspan=2| {{flag|Palau}}\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| 21<ref name=\"Palau Alcoholic Beverage Control Act\">{{cite web|url=http://www.paclii.org/pw/legis/consol_act/babrt11389/|title=Alcoholic Beverage Control Act - \u00a7 1068. Sale or distribution to minors; purchase, possession, or consumption by minors.|publisher=Pacific Islands Legal Information Institute|accessdate=22 March 2018}}</ref>\n| It is prohibited to sell or serve any alcohol beverage to a person under