{{as of|2013}}, the population has increased to 151,088.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov |accessdate=May 22, 2014 }}</ref> The population was 73.1% [[White American|White]], 13.1% [[Asian American|Asian]], 8.0% [[African American]], 7.7% [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race, 2.6% identified as having ancestry of [[Multiracial Americans|two or more races]], 0.4% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], and 0.0% [[Pacific Islander American|Pacific Islander]].\n\nThe median household income for Cary {{as of|2011|lc=y}} was $110,609.\n\n===Educational attainment===\nMore than two-thirds (68.0%) of Cary residents (aged 25 and older) hold an associate degree or higher, and 60.7% of adults possess a bachelor's degree or higher. Cary has one of the lowest crime rates (79% less than [[North Carolina]]) in the state for municipalities of its size.<ref>{{cite web|title=10 safest places to live in the US|url=http://www.clevelandsecuritybloggers.com/10-safest-places-to-live-in-the-us/|publisher=www.clevelandsecuritybloggers.com|accessdate=27 June 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160628182630/http://www.clevelandsecuritybloggers.com/10-safest-places-to-live-in-the-us/|archivedate=28 June 2016}}</ref><ref name='national geographic'>{{cite news | first=Joel | last=Bourne | title=Suburbia Unbound | date= | publisher= | url =http://www.nationalgeographic.com/ngm/0106/feature7/index.html | work =National Geographic | pages = | accessdate = 2007-04-16 | language = }}</ref> The home ownership rate (owner-occupied housing units to total units) is 72.8%.\n\nIn 2013, Cary moved up in the latest rankings of safe U.S. cities and is now considered the third-safest among municipalities with populations of 100,000 to 499,999, behind [[Amherst, New York]], and [[Irvine, California]], according to CQ Press, publisher of the annual \"City Crime Rankings 2008-2009: Crime in Metropolitan America.\"\n\nData from the 2000 Census shows 29.2% of Cary residents are native to North Carolina; 55.2% were born in other states. Additionally, 15.6% of the town's population were born outside the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.carychamber.com/money2.html |title=Money Magazine Article - Part 2 |accessdate=2010-05-23 |publisher=Cary Chamber of Commerce |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090606150159/http://www.carychamber.com/money2.html |archivedate=June 6, 2009 }}</ref>\n\n==Economy==\n===Notable businesses===\n*[[3Dsolve]] \u2013 Simulation software used in training by the military, recently purchased by [[Lockheed Martin]]\n*[[A10 Networks]] \u2013 U.S. public company specializing in the manufacturing of application delivery controllers\n*[[Arista Networks]] \u2013 Computer networking manufacturer\n*[[Cotton Incorporated]] \u2013 Industry trade-group\n*[[Epic Games]] \u2013 Video game developer\n*[[IntelliScanner Corporation]] \u2013 Home and small business organization products\n*[[Lord Corporation]] \u2013 Diversified technology company\n*[[SAS Institute]] \u2013 Large software company and Cary's largest employer\n*[[Western Wake Medical Center]] \u2013 Private hospital\n*[[ABB Group]] - Electrification, Robotics and Industrial Automation conglomerate\n\n===Top employers===\nAccording to the Cary's ''2018 Comprehensive Annual Financial Report,''<ref>{{cite web |title=2018 Comprehensive Annual Financial Report |url=https://www.townofcary.org/home/showdocument?id=21674 |website=townofcary.org |publisher=Town of Cary |accessdate=26 April 2019}}</ref> the top employers in the town are:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n! #\n! Employer\n! # of Employees\n|-\n| 1\n|[[SAS Institute]]\n|5,616\n|-\n| 2\n|[[MetLife]]\n|2,600\n|-\n| 3\n|[[Verizon Communications|Verizon]]\n|2,000\n|-\n| 4\n|Powersteam Services\n|1,993\n|-\n| 5\n|[[Siemens Medical Solutions|Siemens Medical Solutions  USA]]\n|1,600\n|-\n| 6\n|[[HCL Technologies|HCL America]]\n|1,500\n|