y Yow]], former head coach of the women's basketball team at [[North Carolina State University]]\n\n==Accolades==\n* ''[[Money Magazine]]'' Best Place to Live ranked Cary as #5 in the nation in 2006.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://money.cnn.com/magazines/moneymag/bplive/2006/snapshots/PL3710740.html | title = Best Places to Live 2006| accessdate = 2010-05-23 |date =2006| publisher = [[CNN]]| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20061221000332/http://money.cnn.com/magazines/moneymag/bplive/2006/snapshots/PL3710740.html| archivedate= December 21, 2006|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Sister cities==\n{{SisterCities|Cary|four}}<ref name=sister>{{cite web|title=Interactive City Directory|url=http://sister-cities.org/interactive-map/Cary,%20North%20Carolina|publisher=[[Sister Cities International]]|accessdate=5 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141106002801/http://sister-cities.org/interactive-map/Cary,%20North%20Carolina|archive-date=2014-11-06|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://sistercitiesofcary.org/ |title=Sister Cities of Cary |publisher=Town of Cary|access-date=March 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n*{{flagdeco|CAN}} [[Markham, Ontario|Markham]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n*{{flagdeco|IRL}} [[County Meath]], Ireland\n*{{flagdeco|ROC}} [[Hsinchu City]], Taiwan\n*{{flagdeco|FRA}} [[Le Touquet-Paris-Plage|Le Touquet]], [[Pas-de-Calais]], France\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|United States}}\n*[[I-85 Corridor]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikivoyage|Cary}}\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{official website|1=https://www.townofcary.org}}\n* [http://www.carychamber.com/ Cary Chamber of Commerce]\n\n{{Cary, North Carolina}}\n{{Chatham County, North Carolina}}\n{{Wake County, North Carolina}}\n{{North Carolina}}\n{{Triangle, NC}}\n{{North Carolina cities and mayors of 100,000 population}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in North Carolina]]\n[[Category:Cary, North Carolina| ]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1750]]\n