{"title_page": "Andr\u00e9s Oliva", "text_new": "{{short description|Spanish cyclist}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Andr\u00e9s Oliva\n| image         =\n| fullname      = Andr\u00e9s Oliva\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{birth date|1948|12|7}}  \n| death_place   =\n| death_date    =\n| birth_place   =\n| height        =\n| weight        =\n| discipline    = Race\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 =\n| amateurteam1  =\n| proyears1     = 1969&ndash;1974 \n| proteam1      = La Casera \n| proyears2     = 1975&ndash;1977 \n| proteam2      = KAS \n| proyears3     = 1978&ndash;1979 \n| proteam3      = Teka \n| proyears4     = 1980\n| proteam4      = Kelme\n| manageyears1  =\n| manageteam1   =\n| majorwins     = '''[[Grand Tour (cycling)|Grand Tours]]'''\n:'''[[Giro d'Italia]]'''\n::[[Mountains classification in the Giro d'Italia|Mountains Classification]] ([[1975 Giro d'Italia|1975]], [[1976 Giro d'Italia|1976]])\n:'''[[Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]'''\n::[[Mountains classification in the Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Mountains Classification]] ([[1975 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|1975]], [[1976 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|1976]], [[1978 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|1978]])\n}}\n\n'''Andr\u00e9s Oliva''' (born December 7, 1948) was a former Spanish professional cyclist. Oliva was a great climber, so he ended up winning multiple Mountains Classifications. He won the [[Mountains classification in the Giro d'Italia|Mountains Classification]] at the [[1975 Giro d'Italia]] and the [[1976 Giro d'Italia]]. Those were the only two years that Oliva raced the [[Giro d'Italia]]. In the 1975 edition Oliva finished 14th overall, that was his highest finish. Oliva also experienced success at the [[Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]. He won the [[Mountains classification in the Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Mountains Classification]] at the [[1975 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]], [[1976 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]], [[1978 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]. Oliva's highest finish at the Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a was eleventh overall, he did that in both 1978 and [[1972 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|1972]]. He retired from cycling in 1980.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.the-sports.org/cycling-oliva-sanchez-andres-results-identity-s2-c2-b4-o3-w54030.html |title=Cycling - Andres Oliva Sanchez (Spain) : season totals |publisher=The-sports.org |date= |accessdate=2012-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cyclinghalloffame.com/riders/rider_bio.asp?rider_id=859 |title=Cycling Hall of Fame.com |publisher=Cycling Hall of Fame.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://giro.cyclingfever.com/rider.html?sporter_id=11405 |title=Andres Oliva - Rider Statistics Giro d'Italia - By: CyclingFever.com - The International Cycling Social Network |publisher=Giro.cyclingfever.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-09}}</ref><ref>http://www.cyclinghalloffame.com/races/results/results_vuelta_a_espana.txt</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Giro d'Italia Maglia Verde}}\n{{Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a Mountains Classification}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Oliva, Andres}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Spanish male cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Toledo]]\n[[Category:Tour de Suisse stage winners]]\n[[Category:Giro d'Italia cyclists]]\n\n\n{{Spain-cycling-bio-1940s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Andr\u00e9s Oliva\n| image         =\n| fullname      = Andr\u00e9s Oliva\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{birth date|1948|12|7}}  \n| death_place   =\n| death_date    =\n| birth_place   =\n| height        =\n| weight        =\n| discipline    = Race\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 =\n| amateurteam1  =\n| proyears1     = 1969&ndash;1974 \n| proteam1      = La Casera \n| proyears2     = 1975&ndash;1977 \n| proteam2      = KAS \n| proyears3     = 1978&ndash;1979 \n| proteam3      = Teka \n| proyears4     = 1980\n| proteam4      = Kelme\n| manageyears1  =\n| manageteam1   =\n| majorwins     = '''[[Grand Tour (cycling)|Grand Tours]]'''\n:'''[[Giro d'Italia]]'''\n::[[Mountains classification in the Giro d'Italia|Mountains Classification]] ([[1975 Giro d'Italia|1975]], [[1976 Giro d'Italia|1976]])\n:'''[[Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]'''\n::[[Mountains classification in the Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Mountains Classification]] ([[1975 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|1975]], [[1976 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|1976]], [[1978 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|1978]])\n}}\n\n'''Andr\u00e9s Oliva''' (born December 7, 1948) was a former Spanish professional cyclist. Oliva was a great climber, so he ended up winning multiple Mountains Classifications. He won the [[Mountains classification in the Giro d'Italia|Mountains Classification]] at the [[1975 Giro d'Italia]] and the [[1976 Giro d'Italia]]. Those were the only two years that Oliva raced the [[Giro d'Italia]]. In the 1975 edition Oliva finished 14th overall, that was his highest finish. Oliva also experienced success at the [[Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]. He won the [[Mountains classification in the Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Mountains Classification]] at the [[1975 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]], [[1976 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]], [[1978 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]. Oliva's highest finish at the Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a was eleventh overall, he did that in both 1978 and [[1972 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|1972]]. He retired from cycling in 1980.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.the-sports.org/cycling-oliva-sanchez-andres-results-identity-s2-c2-b4-o3-w54030.html |title=Cycling - Andres Oliva Sanchez (Spain) : season totals |publisher=The-sports.org |date= |accessdate=2012-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cyclinghalloffame.com/riders/rider_bio.asp?rider_id=859 |title=Cycling Hall of Fame.com |publisher=Cycling Hall of Fame.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://giro.cyclingfever.com/rider.html?sporter_id=11405 |title=Andres Oliva - Rider Statistics Giro d'Italia - By: CyclingFever.com - The International Cycling Social Network |publisher=Giro.cyclingfever.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-09}}</ref><ref>http://www.cyclinghalloffame.com/races/results/results_vuelta_a_espana.txt</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Giro d'Italia Maglia Verde}}\n{{Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a Mountains Classification}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Oliva, Andres}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Spanish male cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Toledo]]\n[[Category:Tour de Suisse stage winners]]\n[[Category:Giro d'Italia cyclists]]\n\n\n{{Spain-cycling-bio-1940s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lepricavark", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:added short description", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andr%C3%A9s_Oliva"}
